replyContent: Be careful that your power saving mode does not turn off GPS involuntarily. The screen is often a bigger draw on the battery than GPS, so if it is in your pocket most of the time, it will last a long time.

replyContent: Correct. We get this question all the time, but we will not be able to earn those extra stars from you as long as Google won't let us be in Android Auto. No navigation apps are allowed in Android Auto unless said navigation apps are owned by Google.

I first tried BCN when I was climbing an obscure pinnacle in California that is unofficially known as “Cartago Peak.”  Despite having almost no idea how to use BCN or the borrowed phone, I managed to find the tricky route to the summit AND the way back to my car.  I was sold on BCN.  I bought my first smartphone and I’ve been using BCN for all my mountaineering trips ever since.  I create a .GPX file with my route and important waypoints using CalTopo.  Then I load that file into the phone and import it into BCN.  I download CalTopo maps before leaving, and use BCN to help navigate in the wilderness.  I drop a few breadcrumbs along the way to make sure I can find the way back to my camp or my car.  After 30+ years using a map and compass, BCN is pretty intuitive.  It’s like a map, only MUCH better.  The GPS shows me exactly where I am on the map.  It easily shows the distance and heading to my destination.  I can enlarge the map enough that I don’t need reading glasses.  It takes a bit of practice to get the hang of it, but it’s a powerful navigation tool, and it just works.  I haven’t had any problems with it.  I love this app.  Highly recommended.

It's suspicious how just when the developer is moving to a new and expensive monthly subscription model, the original app (one time fee) starts to fail and become buggy.

Spend a small amount of time getting to know this app and it will be ENORMOUSLY useful. It works great offline, no cell service needed; you have to choose areas to download onto your device before you go out and use it. You'll also need to turn on your gps antenna (wait until you get there to save power) and you can set the behavior of how often it determines your location to conserve even more battery power if desired.   I find this FAR more useful than the comparatively low-tech handheld gps devices on the market because my smartphone can process all that data way faster than the old chips using tiny amounts of memory in those traditional handheld gps devices. I can get all kinds of different topo maps, overlay boundary data, private property, etc. Very valuable tool for hunting and hiking. I also recommend bringing an extra battery or a power pack for your phone since using the gps antenna constantly will drain your battery.

I've used this app for 10 years! It's the best. The paid version is worth. I've backpacked across America 4 times, walked across Madagascar and Spain. It does it all.

phone.
Very difficult to download and install maps, very confusing user interface..Spend you $12 on a paper map.
A great app for hikers
A great app when out and about in the great outdoors

not Miles. I.e 1000 yards not .56 miles. Metric units work well and are 
close enough to yards I can convert relitvley easily.
replyContent: Go into setting and choose non metric units.

content:
This program might be great for cartography geeks but is not intuitive in 
use and has a steep learning curve to memorize all its functions.

Just brilliant. I've been using it frequently since 2013 for both cycling and hiking and it's great. It basically converts your phone into a GPS and, of course, it works everywhere where there's satellite GPS signal (regardless of the phone signal).  It effectively replaces the traditional mountaineering GPS and, while I still carry the mountain GPS as a backup in more adventurous mountaineering, I don't really use anything other than this app. Great for loading and downloading maps (for offline use) of different sources and for any country (which is strikingly easy), for loading GPX tracks, and for recording your own GPX tracks. The maps available are excellent and free. They've managed to give you the option to download some of the best maps provided by each country's main mapping institutions (e.g. OS for UK). The 'satellite view' feature is particularly useful for phones which GPS receptor isn't great, like mine. Don't usually do reviews of apps, or pay for apps, but this one is very much worthwhile if you need to navigate in the outdoors.

Best 15 bucks I've spent in a long time. Some little things suck...the 
arrow usually doesn't point in the direction of travel, making my eyes 
explode (how about just a circle?). Can't group symbol changes on big 
imported kmz's or change symbol from default triangle on import. Being able 
to draw simply lines or polygons would be good. Overall super, simple 
worthwhile app.
Does what it says. Very good app.
Brilliant map! Best one for bushwalking or 4wding.

Highly recommend. Can't do without this app it's amazing. Absolutely love 
it . I use it regularly saves carrying loads of maps and you can use it 
offline
Easy to use once you READ THE INSTRUCTIONS. Works all around the globe.

Good mapping app but since the last couple of updates it is very slow 
loading the maps.
So much better than my Garmin Etrex I can hardly believe it.

I made a mistake and bought this app. Not really usrfull, interface way too 
complex

Good app. Wish it had the option to enter way points from the wear app and 
start/stop tracks.

I've used BCN for approx 4 yrs now. I love it! I "out navigate" Garmin's all the time. There are no easier to use navigation apps. I've tried several. This said, to be a navigator takes a level of commitment. It's not the app's fault there's a learning curve. It's taken me several years to figure out all the things I do with BCN on my phone, and Google Earth at home. I now have a hobbyist enjoyment in researching and planning trips. I use BCN for dirt bike exploring in Western US deserts and mountains.  For riding, I use downloaded regions of the CalTopo US 24k map.  Best map available. Provides the most detail. I do not like AccuTerra. I've found too many mistakes in AccuTerra, and overall there's less detail. The coloring of AccuTerra is pretty. That's what caught my eye initially, but so what. Need to run airplane mode to conserve phone battery. I transfer tracks back and forth from Google Earth, both Android GE, and Windows GE. GE is my "base camp" software. GE is the best view of the earth available. Waterproof LifeProof case provides sufficient dustproofing and ruggedizing for dirt bike jarring.

Maybe a way to back up tracks and waypoints automatically? Maybe a way to 
share with other users?
Very useful in the hills. And for recording tracks.
My favorite choice of all apps available for OS navigation. Not the most user friendly interface and takes some learning but does it all ... Big thumbs up from me.
Great topo map coverages. Good tracking. Used off grid with Samsung Galaxy S4 and a small stack of spare batteries. Get two full days hiking per battery charge. Excellent value.
Update caused storage option to change disabling all features in the app. Re-selecting storage in settings fixed.
replyContent: We did not get rid of the Thunderforest maps, and we did not make dramatic changes in the last release. Please check the layers menu and get help if needed.

content: I've been using this app since 2012. It has only gotten better. I highly suggest the accuterra mapset.   This is a must have in the backcountry. Could be a matter of life and death not having a GPS in certain situations. People who havent used this app just dont get it.  One issue I have is sometimes I cant get the pointer/compass to function/orientate properly.  2018 Update. The Accuterra maps I purchased access to in 2012 no longer work. I'm told by Backcountry Mac Support I must now subscribe to something I already purchased. This is consumer fraud, and I will pursue legal action. First step is to file a complaint with my state's attorney general consumer protection division. Most states have consumer protection laws to help combat fraud like this. Too bad Backcountry Mac and Accuterra have decided to try and charge consumers for services they already purchased.
replyContent: No, you do not need to repurchase something you have purchased, and there is no need to make that claim. If you wish to clarify this issue, then reply to this message and the owner of the company will personally respond.

content: Very hard to use.  Not user friendly at all.  For $10 the pro version sucks.

I subscribed at 20 dollars I am still subscribed yet after 11 months I have yet to get a download of a typo. There is no human support that I can find. Think God I never had to depend on it to save a life.
replyContent: What about our helpdesk at support.crittermap.com? If it isn't working, contact us there for resolution or a refund.

I love this app

A great app for hiking, walking and cycling, download offline maps and use GPS without using your data plan, record tracks or import GPX files, great waypoint actions including take a photo and add comments Plus much more 👍👍
Great app!
Great navigating app.

A+ for off-road navigation. Download hi-res sat images and great features for waypoints, routes and interfaces file transfer is easy. £400+ for Garmin or £11 for this app which does more?? No brainer???!

Great

Absolutely marvelous. Been using for 3 years hiking in the mountains. Developer is very responsive to problems, and active in further features. Choose your map style(s), download your area of choice, and away you go - very simple or go complex and detailed. It has got everything. My favorite is exporting my trail into Google Earth. If you were to get stuck on some detail just ask, or there is an extensive online manual. And, that is just the beginning.
Does it work with Android Auto? I couldn't even select it as a map source.
replyContent: No, because Google only allows themselves to make map apps for Android Auto (google maps and waze). Only audio and chat apps are allowed for anyone else.

content: By far my favorite app for offline navigation. Absolutely LOVE the integration with APRSdroid. Outstanding!

There is one feature that at least in my opinion would make this app COMPLETE, and earn 5 stars status from me; I wish I could track my other friends/hunters in our group as we move around while hunting/hiking, of course we all have this app in our phones. That would be the pinnacle of this great app. That to me/us is very important, and my friends and I all agree that with that feature we could move more freely around knowing the we all know where the others are at. Come on BCN, you can do this!!!!  :) Update: 2/13/18: So BCN, when will you come out with your own gps device and teach GARMIN how's done????
replyContent: If your hunting buddies do not have coverage where they want to track each other, there is no way it can be done with current smartphones. If you do, it is possible.

content: Spent 4 days in the Canadian Rockies and before I left, I downloaded various maps at various zoom levels. We even managed to find a couple Geocaching spots to within a couple feet! Canadian Topo maps are detailed & very accurate. Other maps are handy and accurate too.

content: This app is superb!

I use this app when dirt biking or mountain biking, download very detailed hi res OpenCycle maps at zoom level 16 for maximum detail in Australia, once you have downloaded some map tiles use a file manager and go to "internal memory/bcnav/archives" and copy the db to your sd card, you can save as many maps as you like this way and never have to download them again, I have an older sony xperia with a 6 inch screen but limited internal memory, it's just the best for navigation, create tracks in google maps and save as kml or gpx files, you won't regret buying this app...
Great App!  Is there a way to display the waypoint labels text at half size and quarter size like the waypoint icon?

Great application if you enjoy the outdoors. Can purchase overlays for public/private land borders which was alot of help during my hunting season. Tracks altitude and location really well. And the maps are highly detailed.  The only con/negative I have is the maps are slow to download depending on how big of a map you need to download. Outside of this I have nothing bad to say about this application.

I've tried a few GPS apps but always find myself coming back to this one. I like being able to easily import and export gpx files for trips. I now use it exclusively as my hiking and backpacking database making it much easier to do repeat trips in certain areas.
Been using for years. Really useful in the UK with free access to the OS maps (Ordinance Survey; normally the same price for one paper map as the whole app).
I love this app. I use it while elk hunting. You can download maps before going out and put your phone on airplane mode while hunting. Your battery will last forever, almost.
4 or 5 years now and it has saved my life twice....

However, the interface of the BCNavigator together with the improved screen on my phone are so much better than the Garmin.  I depend on it for bushwacking in the mountains and desert.  The cost incredibly small for the value.  This is the best app that I have paid for.
Useful for going off of the beaten path. Ski touring / enduro riding / climbing etc.
Great back country GPS  app with excellent access to maps.  Easy to use.  Great tool for hunters, backpackers, or anyone heading into the wilderness.

I have used this hunting in Tn. TWRA has KML files which you can import I have used this hunting in Tn. TWRA has KML files which you can import as boundaries.  I also downloaded Thai maps and used it out in the country. Worked great on evo and Note 2 plus Galaxy Tab without cell signal. Thanks.

content: Replaces a 200 or 300$ GPS (just make sure you have spare phone battery for long trips). Amazing map sources, also being able to import custom maps is great! Excellent application. There is a learning curve but clear and comprehensive documentation is available online and for download. There are also third party YouTube videos which are helpful. If you are a hiker, a back country camper/explorer, a hunter, a fisherman, etc., then check this application out.

Great android app for mapping with my phone when out of town w/o my mapping tools.  Its a little limited compared to full tools at home but a great tool for spontaneous trips off road.  Love it!

content: I've been using BCN since 2013 and it's still my go to app when I 'm outdoors on one of my adventures. The developer is always making a real effort to update the app and  add new features. I highly recommend this app !
Works very well!

I'm on a sar team and passed my GPS test with this. For ops where theres lots of navigation required or it could go on for a while I'll bring my etrex. But for something where I need the basics, but really don't need days of battery or am not wearing big gloves I'll rock this app only. Spend some real time learning it though, lots of features.
Been using this since 2010. It does all I need and more. The interface is often difficult for me but only because it keeps improving over the years. It's hard for my old mind to keep up.
An excellent app.  The ability to cache maps for when you don't have cell service is great. I use it all the time for four wheeling.
Easy to use. Works great for backpacking.
I used this app as my sole GPS for a weeklong high adventure trip to the Wind Rivers. It worked perfectly. I had offline access to topos, Satalite images, and slope shading.

content: Learning curve is easier when out in field that im familiar with  and getting to trust this app. Hoping to rely on this in unfamiliar territory soon. So far so good. Definitely bring extra battery backup.
Great app more versatile than a GPS device
Best maps i have seen
Offline map work well when Jeeping in the back country.  Having USFS maps with my location marked has saved me from many wrong turns.
Excellent application. Works fine with Moto G (2nd Gen) & Android 7.1. Spain topo map updated by source. Thxs!

I use this for everything from hunting to dirt biking. Most of the places I go do not have service so being able to download maps and use my phone as a GPS is awesome. It's kept me from getting lost on multiple occasions.

This is a really powerful app for off the grid travel once you get used to the system. It's not the most intuitive, but it's really simple once you start using it often. Don't be lazy! Read a bit of the tutorials. I use this for 4WD travel, but have also used it for splitboarding in the mountains. Results can be seen when you export to your computer and viewed via Google Earth. It can be shared to friends, but it's not the easiest. This app uses the compass built into the phone or tablet. If the compass doesn't work, your tablet does not have a built in GPS. You will need to exchange it for one with a built-in GPS. The magnetic compass dial is very accurate. The maps provided are sufficient.  The little things that could be improved: - The location cursor would be nice if it could auto-center, so you don't have to drag the screen as you travel across the map.  - Sometimes when I double tap, the screen zooms into full screen and you don't have access to the controls. - Being able to toggle on/off BLM border views from main menu or screen. Sometimes the markings become annoying which requires you to click through 3 screens to toggle.
Great tracking with great functionality. A bit of time to learning the functions you need and how to use them is rewarded generously.
Works really well in the UK using OS tiles. Offline tends to work better than OS Maps official app. Although I use both (backup to each)
I use this regularly. I love it and I love the layers available. It has never let me down.

Very good app! I use this for moutain biking and hiking in Western Canada. I was going to buy a garmin navigation device but found this app does all that i want without spending several hundred dollars.
How do I get a refund for in in app add on?  Not at all what i expected for an add on layer
replyContent: To discuss your experience with the add on, please contact the helpdesk by replying to this message.

content: Great app but would like the ability to measure distance along a trail or previously traveled Trail

I have switched back and forth between this app (BCN) and Gaia.  My opinion is that BCN has many more powerful features and works fast and flawlessly but that Gaia has an better user interface and is easier for an beginner but not as stable.  I am currently a BCN user and highly recommend it.
Just got a new phone and was disappointed to see that all my waypoints were gone. Great Navi app from my experience.

Solid Backcountry GPS app, but has some interface issues which can make it less user-friendly and intuitive. Some of the terminology used is unclear, and some functions are either in odd places, limited, or non-existent. The most annoying is that you can't move a waypoint once you have placed it, and you have to go to the waypoint list to edit or delete it. Creating and changing trip databases (filing information for a specific trip) is not obvious enough or close enough to the surface. There is no real sharing option, just an import/export that saves the file to your phone, that then you have to go find and attach to an Email or something to get to a computer or cloud storage.  If you want something to share your trip info with others this is not set up to do that easily.

Thank you devs for pointing out that the map magnification is still available and has just been moved from within the settings to the main view. Only thing I would point out is that the symbol is a spy glass and I just assumed it was a new search button as most apps use this symbol for search buttons.  UPDATE: After a recent update we seem to have lost 'Map Magnification' in the settings which used to help with different resolution screens. Now, when I view British OS maps the detail is too small on screen at the point when the map changes from 1:50 000 (Landranger map) to 1:25 000 (Explorer map). Please bring this feature back. If it is still available in the app, please point me in the right direction as I cannot find it in the settings. OLD REVIEW: I have used this app for years for walking and rambling in the UK and also whenever I go abroad. Can't live without it, keep up the good work.
replyContent: You have not lost map magnification. In fact you now have a button at the upper left (unless you turned it off in settings) to do the same thing easier.

content: Brilliant! I'd like to pitch my $800 Android Garmin Monterro in the river. Other than the robust hardware of the Garmin, this app does so much more than the crappy 1990s era Garmin software. And I can trash about 6 cheap tablets in the field and still be ahead. The demo was almost enough but for 16 bucks, the functionality of Pro is priceless. I love the audio waypoint feature...no keyboarding with dirty hands or in foul weather. It's time for Garmin to fade away to auto GPS toys.
Absolute best map app for finding backcountry roads and trails

I feel like it could use a little user interface design love though. It's  not very intuitive at first at all. Once set it is very user friendly but getting it set up is challenging at first. Thanks for making this!

Great app.

This is a great program with almost as many features as my expensive handheld GPS device.  If you  have a problem with the permissions, can't find a feature, or can't figure something out, go to the author's web site and RTFM.  The app author is very responsive and support is excellent. content: Great app. If your into geo location mapping and point plotting and tagging for future referral and sharing this is fantastic.

content: Would have lost the trail using paper maps. This app is great and in aeroplane mode lasted three days of constant referencing. I now want to understand all its other tricks eg distance tool and bearing. Love it!
I've had this app since 2009 and have loved it ever since.

I used the free Demo version for several months while I compared it with several other smart phone hiking navigation apps.  It works great when you are off your phone network and have downloaded your map area ahead of time. I usually put my phone on "airplane mode"  and can go hiking for more that 8 hours with plenty of battery power left at the end of the hike. This is the best. It is the easiest to download and upload GPX files to Garmin Base Camp on my PC. The Pro version lets you store your maps, GPX files and recorded tracks on the phone's external memory card. And if all that is not enough, the staff keeps the Pro users informed of problems, solutions and upcoming improvements. This is the only app on my phone that has such a great staff keeping the users informed.

Update 5/26/17: I have been using the pro version for about two years now and it has paid for itself a hundred times over! I would be happy right now if I had paid $50 for it.   Original review: Just used the pro version on an 6 day hike of Ashley National Forest in Utah and never had to check the paper map once. Loved the ability to add custom waypoints and attach pics to them. No more carrying a GPS and a digital camera for me. My phone now does it all!
Have been using for over 3 years which says a lot. I think it is a most excellent application and when used in conjunction with UK OS  mapping it is awesome!
For someone who has no direction in his life, this app sure does help lead the way. 5 stars.

content: Perfect.  Plenty of features, always improving, great value for money.  I mainly use in the UK with downloaded OS Maps but also use on holidays abroad. I sold my expensive Garmin when I installed this app on my tablet and phone. BackCountry Navigator Pro is very intuitive. I use this almost exclusively for search and rescue work high in the Colorado Rockies. I need to be able to enter coordinates very quickly, and also be able to change coordinate systems quickly, and with this app it is so easy.  This was also the ONLY app I could find that has the USFS maps showing trails in this area that no other maps have. My only quibble (minor) is that on my tablet (Nexus 7) the cursor when I enter the coordinates is a dark green on a grey background. It is not that way on my phone (white cursor). But it is impossible to see in the dark, and only mildly better in a well lit room. So, $350 for a Garmin that never worked properly, or less than $15 for an app that is intuitive, easy to use, and works flawlessly for me. Tough choice! Wish it was available for use on an iOS device so the team could standardize; several Apple users have wanted to use this app.

content: The overall functionality is good, but the UI is atrocious.  It is written like an engineer trying to hit bullet points and not like an artist trying to describe something to you with pictures.  Don't know if you've used a map lately, but it's basically an informative piece of art.  It's better than no TOPO, but I'm thinking there is a better app for doing so more efficiently.  Turning off my purchased BLM Boundary layer requires entering a settings menu, selecting a list filter for Purchased, then clicking on the item, then unchecking "Show on Map".  But, there's a Map Layers button on the main map view... Why is my map layer not selectable via the map layer button?!?!?  6 clicks instead of 2??  In fact there is no way to select ANY layers via the Map Layers button, it is simply used to select the main map source.  Of which you may only select one, so it should at least be called Map Layer.  The purchasing is completely clumsy.  Subscription only maps should be segregated from the free ones to the make the selection process less cluttered.  Is there an order to the way they are displayed?  It sure isn't alphabetical.  Is it the order of how pretty they are?
replyContent: The Map Layers menu *does* have a way to turn overlays on and off, you will see it when you click "Add-on overlays". You do not have to go to purchasing or settings menu.

Once I finally spent an hour or so trying to figure out the basic download of a trail map, start, stop, save and name of the hike it wasn't a good experience. It also put the name of the hike all over the map at least 5 times that blocked the map itself. Trying to go back to see the stats of the hike was just as complicated. If you are looking for a "mapmyhike" type of app for tracking, skip this all together. I wasted $11.99 and way too much of my time trying to figure out the basics of an app.
Worked great while through hiking from Mexico to Canada on PCT and CDT. Strongly recommend! Save my life... Really...
This is the best app for all my  walking easy to " navigate" around the app  very easy to use and then review my walks
I've used this on canoe trips and a five day hiking trip with my daughter to Mount Assiniboine last year. Fantastic!
I've been using BCN for a few years. It's a great mapping GPS tool. Just works for me. Also the best product support you will find.
Still using ancient imagery. Why?
replyContent: If the question is not rhetorical, 1. We can't afford our own satellites. 2. We often rely on government sources and we do not have control over how often they update. 3. Our customers have not been willing to pay for paid subscriptions. 4. We do not have permission (nor does anyone) to save Google Satellite Imagery for offline use.

content: Have been using the PRO version for a couple of years now. Excellent app once you get used to how to use it. I never go an a trip without it!
App works great on moto G for offline maps prebuilt with Mobile Atlas Creator (MOBAC).  Only complaint was fixed after submitting helpdesk request.
★★★★ 5 Star functionality. Job well done. I'm a civil engineeer.  Great choice of topo maps even without mytopos.  5 star support★★★★★

Fantastic for off line navigation one suggestion I would like to add is make the download select area bigger so we can download large areas in one shot instead of having to select many times to cover one area
I download my topo maps and put my phone on airplane mode.  It's a must for hiking.   Been using it for 4 years now and love it.

The best mapping and tracking map for the UK. Download OS maps for use offline. Download gpx tracks into the app for walks which aren't on OS maps (eg Arran Coastal Way). Has never let me down and I don't know what I'd do without it.
It's got a bit of a steep learning curve, but once you get it figured out it's great.

I have really enjoyed using this app with my Samsung S4 (Android 5) and it appears to work flawlessly with good wifi coverage.  However, the necessity to download certain sections of map areas relevant to each trip appears flawed. 1. I used the map section download feature at home to store areas of the Calif Sierra Nevada for a recent backcountry trip.  On the trip I discovered that a number of the stored areas did not have the same resolution as the source map (Cal Topo). 2. In an area of weak wifi but good 4G coverage I was unable to access the online source map???  Result was that the app was useless.  I do not understand why the full source map that would easily fit on a SD card cannot be stored on my device.  This would eliminate the annoying pick and choose type of storage which is inconvenient or unworkable in areas of marginal coverage.   The beauty of this app is topo map coverage and GPS location in non 4g-wifi signal areas but its useless without properly stored maps.
replyContent: The full source map of Caltopo does *not* easily fit on your storage. However, if you use state size maps from openandromaps.org/en, they can.

content: If I pay £10 I DO NOT expect a notification telling me to press for more information repeatedly popping up, I do so and there is nothing new??! Fix it or refund please!
replyContent: What pop up notification? Not entirely sure what you are talking about, but help screens can be taken away if you push the checkbox button on the lower left.

content: So useful. Real time location spot on.

I love this app.  There is only one thing that I haven't seen implemented yet. Have any of the developers even thought of, or even considered having the option of showing an ETE or ETA to a waypoint?!?  Really, that's the only thing keeping it from 5 stars.  Lets get that in there!! Thanks.

Anyway you could add block management boundaries as an add on layer for montana? This would complete the whole package for montana. And is there a way to shade the whole state/ public land blocks rather than just an outline?  Thanks

replyContent: Since there are worldwide maps, plus country maps at OpenAndroMaps,  there are no countries that are not available.

content: Used this app all weekend. Excellent

I used it a lot with different  free maps. Pluses - easy to import tracks and way points, does not use much of battery, smartphone battery last for 6-7 hours hikes. If map is detailed enough it is easy to navigate and find you way - unless the compass shows wrong direction which (a) happened quite a lot and (b) unpredictably. Maybe it was  because of old Android phone.
replyContent: Check the compass screen and see if changing algorithm settings makes a difference.

content: Does more than it says on the tin! Clear fast rendering of OS maps at all scales with comprehensive Help screens. Track recording by GPS off-line, low battery use, and easy saving of map sections to SD card make this a winner app, even better than OS Maps and half the price as a one-off payment of the annual subscription to OS. Best app I've downloaded!

I've used the app in some very remote locations of SE Oregon. As much as I rely on my BLM maps, BCN has more detail and tracks for me. I still carry paper and compass, but this app has definitely upped my confidence levels to expand my skills. I also love the pin feature... I can mark sites I want to revisit for night photo ops.  Thanks for such a useful tool.

As a hiker, biker, motorhome traveller, etc. I find that I use this app more than any other on my phone (OK, I don't use social media apps). I used to use a pedometer to keep track of distances hiked, but this has replaced that (and is much more accurate). Also, the free Andromaps have been especially useful when travelling to other states.
Confusing at first but worth the money
Reliable and substantial

I didn't find it any easier (or less expensive) to just purchase physical topo maps instead. Tried to reach out to the developer for a refund, only to receive a snarky response. You'd do well just to pass on by this app & not waste the money

Shot several nice bucks thanks to this app

content: I have used this app for years, on multiple different devices, including: Droid X, HTC Rezound, Moto X (2013), and Droid Turbo 2. I edited my review to 2 stars after verifying the performance impact on all of my devices.
replyContent: I suggest removing folders under bcnav/tiles and using Saved Map Folders for future downloads instead of Main Tile Cache. This helps on devices that are sensitive to many small files.

content: Does what it is supposed to do with a minimal of fuss. The documentation is good and should be read through prior to going hiking,hunting, etc...download the maps before heading out!
Used for many years on 3 different phones. Never lets me down.

content: Best navigation, I have seen so far for Android.
Perfect mapping app for UK outdoors 5 star

No more paper maps and GPS for me, this app does it all.  Download any map for free and use the GPS that's in my phone.  Shows my exact location on the map.  No cell coverage needed and with phone in airplane mode, the battery goes all day with only 50 to 75% drain.
Simple to use, easy for off grid backpacking, uses maps downloaded, outstanding app.

Using this on my Note 4 instead of using a traditional handheld GPS unit means that I have longer battery life, a larger and better-quality screen, a thinner device, and an all-around better experience.  I also don't have to spend $100s for the extra device either!
How do I get reimbursed found a better app

This is the best gps app that I have found, use it for back packing, hunting and fishing. Download the areas you need before going afield, put your phone in airplane mode and enjoy the outdoors. Highly recommended!

Absolutely the best app for UK outdoor navigation. the best I have tried, and I've tried a few!!! Now that my nephew has shown me how to transfer recorded routes to my PC it's even better

I use this all of the time with the accuterra subscription.  The ability to download high quality maps and use them where no service exists is unparalleled. I just got back from camping and exploring in SE Oregon for 10 days and this app never let me down even though I had no service for most of it. Works really well. Brilliant app totally reliable. Used it everyday on two weeks of hiking, it never missed a beat. This app should be one of the markets top apps.  This has seen an amazing amount of use. I would never want to be without this app. Totally reliable and brilliant, I use in UK with OS mapping. This is a great app, I liked it on my phone and love it even more on my new Galaxy Tab 4 8.0. The bigger screen really helps. I use it on outings with my 4x4 club. I live where cell phone coverage is nonexistent, once you get out of town and off road. It's easy to use, just download maps ahead of time for use off line.
Great for UK as it has OS maps. So easy to set up for off-line use. Good user interface. Used it a lot for 3+ yrs in UK on Samsung S4.
Extremely happy with this app. Offline maps works well with just a little pre-planning.

I am very satisfied and it is still being improved. Major update in progress.. I'll add to my comments. It works. Stop complaining and ask questions.and learn. These guys go out of their way to help you. I have used it for a long time and I feel that I more than got my moneys worth.

Great app for hiking and off-roading. Frequent  updates bring constant improvements. Accuterra maps (cost extra) are worthwhile for trails.  Update: I bought this app and some of the extra-cost maps several years ago (too many to remember) and it continues to be top-notch for topo maps. Some people seem to have trouble using it and leave comments that say that offline maps don't work or similar stuff, I can only recommend you try the free trial version is see for yourself and contact the authors if you're having trouble.

Samsung Galaxy 5 This is an excellent app.  May take a little to get used to how to use it but it allows you to take detailed electronic maps into the backcountry.  The map quality is limited by the available downloads.  Here in NZ we have free maps down to 1:50,000 so you only loose quality when you zoom in beyond this resolution - this is no fault of the app developer but depends on the data source.  I have used them outside NZ and haven't been able to find such good map sources (but I didn't try hard).  It doesn't use that much battery and can record a track to work out where you went wrong on an orienteering exercise after you have finished.  This is well worth the money.  I have only had to contact support once and they were quick to respond with very helpful advice and a clear desire to get the problem sorted.  I can't compare with other apps as I haven't seen the need to try them.  This does everything that I wanted an off-line mapping app to do:  well done!

If you read a review of this product complaining there are no offline maps there is nothing further from the truth.  This product has many offline options but the user must pre plan and download maps of the area of interest as is explained in the user guide.   People who expect a $12 app to have maps for the world  already installed simply do not understand how GPS maps work on cell phones.  Even Google maps does not work unless connected to a network via a cell carrier or via WiFi.  In my opinion this is one of the best mapping apps on the market.  I have used this tool in the back country and on the water and find it to be very useful.
Best off line GPS EVER! It does take some preplanning to download the areas where your going. It's worth the price just to get Nathan's newsletter.

Excellent

content: Works great. I have a pricey Delorme GPS that I dont even use anymore.

To be fair, by all accounts, BackCountry Navigator is the best.  BUT, it falls way short of what is necessary.  It may be possible that I have not been able to figure out some of these features, in which case I would argue that the developer should make these features easier to use.  I did purchase and use the Pro version.  I recently relied on BackCountry Navigator in a mountain hike that was way off the grid.  I did download the correct TOPO map before leaving and I set some waypoints but, I was unable to retrieve the waypoints after I was off the grid.  The map was there.  The actual trail varied from the trail marked on the map  numerous times, sometimes by over 100 feet.  I found that I needed two other apps to give me the information I wanted.  I used an altitude app and I used a popular walking app that tracked time,distance and pace.  It was a pain having to switch between apps while hiking on a rocky trail.  I recommend that the developer add (or make more useful) the following features (and many features related to these):  Altitude,  Pace,  Distance traveled, Save stats locally (for off grid use).  The app should only earn a 5 if it is rich in features.

Use this app all the time.  I did prefer the markers pre update but it's easy to use and quite functional.  I find it works fine even when I have no cell service provided I have the map area loaded beforehand

content: Used it for years.

content: Just returned from a several week trip where I finally got to use this app in depth. There *are* tutorials, like this one. http://support.crittermap.com/entries/22108757-Choosing-Map-Sources

content: Only app needed for downloading external maps and GPX files for a truely useful GPS on your phone. And the best electronic compass I've seen yet.!!!

Awesome app! Thank you BCN for keeping it open to custom user maps unlike some of the other guys!  I am proud to say we’ve had great success with the OFFROAD ATLAS mvum maps!

Use it to track my hikes.  Also, a friend has produced a detailed map of the forests where I backpack with up to date trails, etc.  BCN is prefect for this use.
Perfect app! And the developer listens to any input on it! Thanks for fixing the compass. :)
Works great

Use the help screen and email button to send us a log. 
A blocking problem like this is usually a failure to write to storage. Phones have been known to change permissions on storage volumes in firmware updates. See also the helpdesk for a tip that may help.

content: Love the the lifetime price. Easy functionality and offline map cache.

content: Great way to explore backcountry without getting lost!

March '15 update:  Vastly improved from 5 yrs ago, when its glaring omissions led to an immediate refund. Excellent strengths (especially relative to Gaia) incl.: - extensive map library (option aerial imagery w/ topo lines is especially valuable for above-treeline ski mountaineering) - ability to set up multiple trip databases (i.e., segregating waypoints & tracks from different regions). Major problems for serious navigation though include: - a Stat screen that displays every conceivable piece of navigational data yet a Nav screen that displays only the compass rose, heading, bearing, and distance while leaving ~1/3 of the screen empty, i.e., which could be used for add'l important data items; - lack of any proximity alert when navigating to a waypoint (i.e., just have the phone beep w/in ~10m so you don't have to keep staring at the screen).
I have used a number of GPS mapping apps.  This would be one of the top apps. It is not as easy to set up as the opposition but has many great features buried in it.
This is one of the best app I use.
replyContent: Glad you like it.

content: Update Jan 2016 - Still going strong. I've used this on several phones and tablets since I bought it and even written guides on how to use it for folks. As good as ever and now supports Vector Maps from OpenAndroMaps. Still absolutely brilliant and my main choice for backcountry maps and offline maps.  ----  This has been a fantastic purchase that I've used for several years for all of the following: Snowshoeing - including several trips into the British Columbia backcountry,  Hiking - just like snowshoeing, Backcountry Skiing, Backroad driving, Cycling, both on the roads and off them. There are a great deal of maps available, just some of my favourites are: OpenStreetMap, CalTopo's scanned maps (which are great for BC), Canada Toprama, NRCan (Natural Resources Canada), Multimap (United Kingdom Ordinance Survey Explorer Maps) and there are many more. Honestly, I will never be short at least some sort of map.  Further, the simple power of downloading maps for offline use is incredibly useful and can add a use to your phone you just didn't expect to be using it for.  Recommended!

Still only getting started in using this App. Keep up the good work.

BCN cannot route.  That is, you cannot enter a waypoint or POI and have BCN navigate you to the destination. All it can do is show your location on a map and create a track and it doesn't do either well.  The maps suck. They are huge bitmap files that look like a paper map.  So when you zoom out the text does not scale and you can't read anything.  When driving South all text and map features are upside down.  The map download process limits you to a very small area because of file size.  No night mode. ...
replyContent:
YES you can.
Most of what you say is not true. 
You CAN enter a waypoint and have BCN navigate you to the destination. We call it GOTO. 
I understand that you object to raster/image maps, but there are great scaling vector maps at OpenAndroMaps with one button installation. 
You CAN turn off map rotation.

content: Awesome app, been a ozi explorer user forever, but this leave ozi for dead, is a shame there isn't anymore maps for Australia other than east coast, the topo  mosaic online map is great but even better when downloaded so we can get truly lost and then find our way home easily would like to know if we can use AccuTerra Topo Maps for Australia also or you just spoiling the yanks
replyContent: Accuterra Maps does not cover Australia, so it wouldn't help. There are worldwide and OpenAndroMaps covering there. If you know of a map supplier in Australia who will work with us at an affordable price, send them our way.

content: uninstalled. Started sending me spam notifications; no thank you I do not care about your openandromaps whatever that you want me to watch a youtube video about how to buy. I wish I could get my money back, but here we are.
replyContent:
It is not an advertisement. 
OpenAndroMaps are free. 
It is a notification of a feature few are aware of. If not interested, that's fine. 
But if this bothers you, please talk to us about a refund.

content: Excellent Route planner and easy to use GPS on both my Android tablet (Nexus) and my Moto E 2nd Gen. Very easy to transfer GPX files between the two using ES Explorer Pro.
Been using this for years now and have almost replaced my Garmin.
Massive battery drain when not in use after latest update.  22% -27% a day when not being used. With gps always on option disabled. Please look into battery drain.
replyContent: I do not believe the battery drain is from us. Please contact the Helpdesk with the evidence you have.

content: Best app ever
Easy to understand and everything works very well
An excellent app. No longet need  a stand alone GPS
Very valuable when packing in with my horses to camp in the high country. The land ownership and game unit overlays can be critical knowledge.
Nice
if you have true GPS on your phone this works great.
Love it!
Easy to use. Easy to send a screen capture to a friend to share location information. This app replaces my hand held GPS for 90% of my back country navigation.
I would give 5 stars if it had property ownership maps to aid you while hiking or hunting. Other than that this app is everything it says it is.
Great GPS app!

Tried it on 3 hunting trips. Spent the money and downloaded maps. App still crashes and provides pixelated maps. I thought by downloading the maps this wouldn't happened. Maybe good if you near a WiFi hot spot.
replyContent: Sorry to hear that. A wifi hot spot is not required. Please contact us for diagnosis or reimbursement.  You can send a log after a crash by using the Help Dialog and the Email HelpDesk button.

content: Great app

I've been using this app for a couple of months now and I have found that it's not real easy to figure out. Yes, there are help screens, which are helpful to a point, but if you've never used this type of tracking navigation app before it can be a bit frustrating. I read a lot of the reviews before purchasing the Pro edition and did find that playing with it as much as possible has made it somewhat easier to understand but I have tracked several day hikes I've done only to loose them somewhere on my phone. I save the trips but not sure of the different ways to save and how to retrieve what I've saved. If there was a tutorial one could watch it may be helpful. Update 12/2015 - This is an excellent app to have. I use it on every hiking and backpacking trip I go on. It's become a very valuable tool for me. Being able to download the maps you need for your hike and then use them off line is great.
replyContent:
Push the folder icon on the top of the screen. Push "Choose Another Trip Database". 
Those two buttons solve most issues of people looking for their previous tracks. 
Stay tuned for a video on the topic.

content: I love this app. It is fantastic. But when can we get an audible alarm that sounds if we veer off a track that we are following? Need this feature!!!!!!!!!!!!

Lost all my waypoints after an update.  Also, I signed up for subscription to premium package but got less than a year before I received notification my "trial" was over.  Love the features, great app!   Some of the built in maps are now premium maps which I don't like.
replyContent: Contact us if you don't think your subscription lasted as long as it should.

content: Great app for new lease.

Love this app and all the flexibility it provides.  Last night, we were on a remote trail in an area we were not familiar with.  It got dark before we could start heading back.  This app showed us the available trails and even though we found several dead ends, we did make it home safely without getting lost.  I really feel confident we may still be there without this app.

BCN Pro has been extremely useful for me.  I have used it mostly for mapping purposes.  I manage an irrigation association in a remote area of Montana, with multiple miles of creeks, reservoirs, and canals, and hundreds of irrigation structures, diversions and turnouts.  I use this app to collect accurate gps "waypoints" for later transfer to a custom map of our system.  Also used for personal trekking.  I haven't had any real issues with BCN that are the fault of the app.  With Android 4, there were issues with storing map files to SD card, but with Android 5 those issues are mostly resolved.  That's Android, not BCN.  I've also had issues at times with getting gps readings, but that is issue with my tablet, and again not BCN.  Basically, any functional issues that I've had are not due to the app itself.  This developer is quite dedicated to it, and provides updates on a continual basis.  I've read reviews with complaints about the "hidden" charges for maps.  These are false issues, I use both satelite & topo maps that are provided free.  There are "some" maps also available that do require a fee, but they are not required.  Many thanks to the developer.  Worth twice the price.
Finally, an app that really does what it claims to.
Love how they constantly improve the app
Fantastic app.
It's always improving!!!

Great app. Great map choices. Great tech support, resolves issues correctly. I use this app every weekend to plan and take off road jeeps adventures. has not  left me lost yet. make sure you pre-download maps for your area before you go out and its perfect. Only wish the downloaded maps sizes could be bigger than 2gb..but i just download quadrents.
I searched for nearby trails and found great sources for trails nearby. So many great features!!

Used on my recent thru hike of the Pacific Crest Trail with no issues. I especially appreciated the flexibility to import kml trail data from Halfmile. I'll definitely continue to use this as my primary navigation tool on future long distance hikes!
Excellent tool to acquire and use detailed topo maps. Works fine in the Backcountry far from cell or WiFi connection s.
Best hiking app ever...
Great GPS App
Great app for getting back to the woods.   Takes a bit of learning but will do everything your GPS will.
Works offline with downloaded maps and tracking seems to works good...
Accterra backcountry Navigator
Amazing!
By far the best out there nothing else even comes close.
replyContent: Glad you are having fun with it.

content: Use it all the time for backpacking, canoeing, kayaking, driving in areas without cell coverage.  Bit of a learning curve to start but powerful tool once you get past that.
Great App
Very useful tool in the bush.
Updates on a regular basis, use it all over the country and also to track progress when training for the Fandance run on the Brecons

I bought many apps over my years of using android. But this is by far the best app ever purchased. If you like the outdoors and you want to use the GPS on your phone with full mapping this is the app you need! I use this for scouting, stand locations, planning out hiking trips and so much more. I mainly use my phone as my GPS with a backup of a Garmin fenix on my wrist. But when it comes to making trails and stand I always use back country nav to record my data! Buy it now.....
Great for outdoor activities, can't fault it. Highly recommended. LG 3G.
I am enjoying the heck out of this. Good functionality, better than many far more expensive mapping programs.
The app offers some really great functionality but the User Interface is so confusing and poorly designed. Really need a redesign to make the product much more user friendly.
replyContent: Lets talk at the helpdesk about what you would like to see.

content: I'd be great if there were more shapes available in select tool.. Or somehow save the area so you could update the maps without redrawing.
Love this thing, esp with Acuterra add-on.  Finally, all the 24k maps I could want in my pocket!
This app has all the maps I require for my outdoor activities. Excellent!
The best offline GPS app -  wish there was an ios version

Been using open cycle (downloaded built-in) in Patagonia (Chile & Argentina). Works great! Distances, where I am, speed, direction, altitude, pressure, etc. No data connection needed--just a good view of the GPS constellation.
replyContent: Glad to see it used in South America.

content: Great app

This app is one of the best apps I've ever purchased. It does everything I need especially when trying to find waypoints that are out in the middle of the woods. I love the ability to download the different maps from the different sources as well. Thank You developers!

The first thing you have to understand is this is not for novices. It is not a Google Maps. It is a serious piece of GPS software for use when you're off the grid. It has a number of powerful features that you'll need to get familiar with before they will work for you. Once you do it, however, you'll find that this software can replace any stand alone gps device. Try different maps and you'll be amazed at what it can do.
Very handy!

At last! The link to Tasmanian LIST TOPO maps has turned a fairly handy app into a 'must have' companion if you're venturing into our beautiful wilderness areas. My Asus Zenfone 5 is now a fully functional navigation tool. Thankyou.
I use this  app a lot while hunting here in BC Canada. Any new map packs ever come  out? A satellite  type view like Google Earth would be cool as well as hunting region overlays.

All I get when I try to download the New Zealand topomaps is a screen full of crosses and no map details. It could be I am missing something in the instructions which are not great. Come on Devs it should've be this hard.
replyContent: Hey, John. As far as we can tell, you may have done it all right, but NZ Government agency was having server issues which have since cleared up. This is not something we can always control and not something we did just to make it hard.

content: Does what I need. UK OS maps are what I need and the app works great for me.  Not sure what would improve it. Brilliant mapping app. Looking forward to trying Australian maps I read about recently in an email from the developers.
Great app, used it in VT, NH and ME with no wifi and saved on my device topos, worked great. Doesn't get any better!
LOVE it!!!
I use this for work and personal time. There is no combination of apps that could replace it.

I've used this app on hikes in two different wilderness areas here in New Mexico. The navigation is as good as any stand alone GPS unit I've used, and the maps had details on them that allowed me to find abandoned and unmarked trails and roads. Very cool! It also gives you an impressive amount of data about your saved tracks. It's not the easiest app to use, but there's a ton of tutorials that pop up. All in all, great app... First one I've ever rated five stars.
Very good

This application is not for a non technical user.   I should have downloaded a free application!  I missed it if in the app description you identified skills and/or experiences required in order to successfully use this application.     I, as several other reviewers wrote, build a pdf user guide file that can be downloaded and used offline.  This would be of great help to jump start me.  The developer's responses were not user centered.  My device's box came with a printed user guide inside.  And there is available a softcopy user pdf guide.  OS updates are documented online.  Why not here?     Your pre-purchase coolaid was good going in but not filling!   I have made a mistake and recommend anyone else in similar shape bypass this application.
replyContent: I would like you to write into the helpdesk and tell us what skills or experiences you think you need to have. There is an online guide and inline help in the app. If you want to apply for a refund please contact us.

content: Great app
Love how I can save my tracks and way points. Must have going into the woods.
A great work in progress. Looking forward to even more great features. . Thanks.

Hard to navigate, "Help" needs to   written for us old guys to understand. It seems good when it works but loses saved tracks, cannot get back to full maps to select new areas.  Sorry I paid for PRO version. Unistalled the reinstalled, the 2 missing tracks showed back up, now missing the latest one,   once again " did not realize learning curve was so difficult
replyContent:
Sorry you've had such a bad experience. Apply for a refund if necessary. However, it has not lost your tracks. Push Trip Data then Choose Another Trip Database and you will see at least two choices. You recorded two tracks in one and the last one in another. 
Yes, you can get back to choosing full map. Go to Layers menu. Toggle it back to Online.

content: I like the app, it gets regular updates and works on my Samsung devices. Liked the recent mapping additions for Europe.
This is a must have App for Walking and Hiking trails/routes. Deserving 5 stars. Tom
I've used since it first came out and it keeps getting better!

I rely on this software when I'm out of coverage and need to know where I am. It's not intuitive to set up, I'm a tech person and struggled to figure out how to get the right files downloaded and stored in the right place and then viewable. Occasionally I still can't figure out what it's doing. I use it for mostly for browsing NZ Topo maps, if there was some way of downloading the whole country or at least each island easily it would be great. I've also used it to view some open maps for Fiji, which work OK

This is a great app!  Once I figured out how to use it (the developers could certainly do a better job with the User Guide) - it is easy to use  and very powerful.  With this paid version, you get free access to topo maps for the US and all over the world that you can download onto your phone memory for use in the backcountry or just traveling where there is no internet signal.  This app does virtually everything my Garmin GPS unit does in terms of helping me navigate in the backcountry. At $12, this is a heck of a deal!  A must for anyone who hikes or skis into the backcountry.  Or just for bike trips, etc.
Excellent for off road exploration in the UK with the OS explorer maps.
Like using on my Nexus 7 for easy viewing for off road. A few bugs from time to time but they are quick to catch and update. A+ App!
Don't trust the compass
replyContent:
That's largely dependent on the device and not software. 
You can calibrate your phones compass by waving the phone in a figure eight pattern. 
There are settings to base rotation on moving direction, if you prefer.

content: Allows me to save maps offline and use when in the mountains.  I can have both a top and sat view saved and switch between the 2 without losing where I am.  Perfect for finding where you want to go, then  viewing what the terrain looks like.

GPS location takes up to a half hour to find if I'm way out in the backcountry but has definitely gotten me through some gnarly bushwhacks. Easy to modify waypoints but no options to do the same for tracks. Waypoint icons need to be sorted better. Travel statistics only work when GPS is on, naturally, but takes time for the stats to get an accurate average reading.

I've been using this app for about five years or so. I had issues with earlier versions, but it's all good now. This app has served me well countless times hiking and off-roading, and I've recommended this app to many people. It does everything my handheld GPS unit does plus more, and the BLM Land and Deer Zone overlays are really useful too.

Great app.  Used on 10 day backpacking trip in Sierra Nevada - downloaded maps in advance and used to record tracks of our hikes.  Also use for walking in woodlots - used Google Earth Pro to establish property boundary lines, downloaded to phone and was able to monitor my location on the property
User unfriendly. Help is no help. I found some trails I want to explore but, getting navigation to them seems impossible. I feel ripped off.
replyContent: No need to feel ripped off. If it doesn't work for you, contact us so we can make it right.

content: I use this app in bird, wildlife and vegetation surveys. Replaces GPS and aerial maps. Downloaded points directly from Garmin and I can see the whole route with points. Attach pics of points. Awesomist app.
GPS topo maps, best out there!
Use it hunting and playing in the outdoors with the dogs!
Love this app!  Easy to use, loads of waypoint icons and you can save maps for offline use.  I also like the export to Google or email option.
Superb tool to get me around with hires maps
Need more canadain content.  Map cuts off half way in the area I paid for.
replyContent:
What map source? What area? 
I don't think we have paid sources for Canada, so you may need to talk to us at the help desk.

content: Great app. Nice to be able to export all your photos and features in one kmz. Unfortunately,  our company still uses iPads for all our fieldwork because GIS Pro has Bing and Google Map Imagery. I know there is copyright issues, but all you have to do is make it so you can't actually download those maps to your phone. It still works offline cause you just need to cache those spots.
I have the paid version and I love it! The only question I have is there a nautical map I can download that shows water depth?
replyContent:
On US Coasts or Great Lakes, yes. 
Try ENC Online Map Source.

content: I'm still finding my way around this brilliant app.   But so far as helped in finding footpaths to follow on our walks.   And the ability to overlay other users walks  is great.

I use this app lots for hiking and cycling in France usually in conjunction with a paper IGN map. However, the free maps are really of a high enough quality that they can be used alone. Paying the one-off fee for the pro version is well worth it.
Love it

I have been using BackCountry Navigator for several months on a Samsung SGH-T959D. The application is Excellent and Canadian maps are as good as they were on my previous GPS device. Play with BCN for an hour or two and it becomes easy to use. There is some delay in establishing an initial GPS fix on the Samsung that has not totally been solved but I don't think that is the fault of BCN as it has been reported by others using other mapping applications. I highly recommend this application.  After another year has gone by I can say that Nathan, the developer, really has the best interests of his users at heart.    BCN is evolving nicely and Nathan maintains contact with purchasers, sending tips and offering explanations why things work the way they do (provided the user subscribes).  I have replaced my Samsung with a Google Nexus 4 and have noticed much better GPS response. September 2015. The best just keeps on getting better.  I am a mapping junkie and have used a variety of mapping applications.  BackCountry Navigator,is the best off road application I have used.  Occasionally an update might cause a headache but the developer is VERY quick to fix problems. Worth every penny.

Very nice app.  Lots of 'inline' help available while using.  I'm considering the Accuterra subscription for its enhanced trail info.  I'd really like to be able to download the excellent Nat. Geographic Topo map data to BackCountry Navigator (obviously for money) rather than have to use their 3rd party app, which apparently is not as good as BCN.    Could resort to combining pictures of sections of their paper maps, but that sounds quite difficult with all the zoom levels you'd like.

I submitted a helpdesk message on this ... but after doing the update to the most recent, the pro version wouldn't load at all it just hung there.  I uninstalled it and reinstalled and now the pro version will load, however, I lost "everything"; settings, downloaded maps, tracks, trips, "everything" is gone.    Been using the pro for quite some time now and had a lot of history that is now gone, what really sucks as this last weekend I took my son out for his first back country trek and this is data now toast ...  Really desperately needs a backup/restore feature ...!

I'm not an avid backpacker, but I've relied on this app in Scandinavia and New York's Catskills and Adirondacks (maybe South Korea, can't recall). It's a really powerful application with tons of features and capabilities. I love it.
I really like this app, and I use it all the time for jeeping. The UI is not intuitive, but it is serviceable.
Best app on the web
Hands down, this is my favorite app!  A must have for anyone who spends time in the back country.

I tried this app a couple years ago and found it complicated and difficult to manipulate with various tiles and such. Most of the issue was my own ignorance of how these apps worked.  Just recently tried it again and WOW - tons of improvements over previous version. Simple to use, and tracked our 4-wheeling trip with great accuracy. Love this for mapping out our trips, tracking our actual route, and most importantly, pin-pointing my location while on the trails. Spent 6 hours off-roading, and battery on my Samsung Note 3 was still at 60% when we completed the trip for the day.  Absolutely recommend this app
I used this app navigating in the Owyhee backcountry.Worked  like  a champ  with the Accuterra maps I had downloaded on my phone and tablet.

9/8/15 still using the app and now my family and friends use it. (HTC DNA) App works great on airplane mode and is easy to use. Used it all day and still had battery life left at end of day 9/5/12(HTC  incredible) Ploted my hunts and blood trail this last weekend here in Oregon.  Works 100% better then my friends garmin or magellan . So worth every penny. Thanks
So appreciative of the hard work put in by the devs,  Shame I just updated to 4.4 on a Samsung let's see the probs it throws up. ............Update...no probs with 5.1
Fantastic trail aid

I used this app while fly fishing in Wyoming this summer.  It allowed me to find new places to fish while avoiding private land.  Sometimes ranchers just don't like people fishing on their ranch.  I just wish there were more than five stars to give!  However, don't forget to download the maps you will need while you have access to Wifi.
The $20 upgraded maps are also worth while. Shows most of our local trails (Santa Fe, NM)

I have used this for about 5 years on my S4 as a general GPS while hunting and finding old wooden dams in NZ and find it accurate and easy to use. With no cell phone coverage required is a great tool and a cheap app. Well done to the developers.
Great app for any outdoor activity and fantastic value compared to maps and expensive GPS devices
This app rocks!  Intuitive interface.  Offline maps are great.  Routes, waypoints and tracking work flawlessly.  It's the only app I use when in the backcountry.

Purchased pro version after demo use and have used all over western U.S.  It's a huge plus being able to download sources before going off the grid; however, on my tablet with Android 4.4 it is useless because can't write to SD card (Android's fault). Source selection is great, but some unfortunately cost extra.  The app is great for creating way points, looking for USFS camping/trails, measuring distances, and approximating elevation, which I use to verify, or set my Garmin Edge 500 computer's altimeter.
replyContent: It is NOT impossible to use SD Card as of 4.4. We are simply restricted on what folders as described here: http://support.crittermap.com/entries/67437220-Using-External-Storage-

content: I have been using this for years and it is even better than my expensive GPS hand held units. The ability to download maps for out of phone service areas along with being able to plot a coarse on Google Earth and import it to the app are awesome!

Versatile app that is frequently updated. Great selection of maps. Map and storage allows use of app without an internet connection. Bargain! - - Update - -  After a couple of years of use,  and several phone upgrades later,  this app continues to evolve and get better. I have used it extensively in Europe without fail,  and to the amazement of my companions. This is a great mapping investment.
Does everything I need it for, used a lot for hunting and getting around the hills. Easy to use and understand after a couple of times. Highly recommended
One of the best offline map tools.
An easily configurable, fully featured navigation app that's a pleasure to use! Excellent!

Always reliable, always useful. Have personally used it on dozens of multiday mountain bike and running adventures - great for navigation and tracking, perfect for low-battery use by setting longer position record intervals (up to 30 minutes even!)
Great app, customer service seond to none.

This app, my cell phone, and the solar charger have become my main navigation tools on and off trail. This is a flexible in-depth program was lots of map databases to choose from, lots of powerful functions for both pre trip planning and actual execution on the trail. It also keeps track of your progress for post trip storage inter collected database of your hikes.
This is by far the best thing on my phone.
I have used this for several years now, on phone & tablet. Its Useful to download areas before camping or cycling, GPS does the rest. I wouldn't be without it, one of my favorite apps.
Does everything I want plus more.
Great mapping app.  I use it all the time.
BCN is the most important app and the only one that I would miss if I lost my phone. I've used it around the world when trekking with friends that have other devices and BCN is the best.
Great tool for using OS maps for free. All footpaths are shown and are easy to follow.
I use it to plot fire's
replyContent: :) Good luck with the fires. I hear there is quite a lot of them this year

content: I could go on and on about the features of this app that I like.  I use it for camping, backpacking, scouting, hunting.  No other app I've tried knocks outdoor activities out of the park like this one!
replyContent: Good to hear.

content: I love this app.

This app is very useful for my rockhounding, camping, hiking, and geocaching needs. I have had some issues with predownloaded maps not displaying occasionally and sometimes refreshing quite slowly when switching between zoom levels.
replyContent: When you have problems like that, its worth checking to see if you are experiencing storage or file corruption.

content: If you fish,hunt,hike of the beaten paths this is a must have ,works better and more features then most handheld units.
App worked phenomenally.  When our trail was covered by water because of the Beavers we were able to find our way on a map.
Very good I recommend this app
A brilliant map program. I needed an off road with offline maps. This is ideal and a great price.

Excellent resource for planning and navigating through the backcountry. I have been using this app since 2010. It has worked on every android device I have owned, from $20 pre-paid phones to the high-end flagship phones.  I never leave home without it. Hiking in the Colorado Rockies, exploring the Mojave, day trips through Appalachia, geocaching, and currently using it to plan and customize an upcoming #TransAmericaTrail expedition.
Used relentlessly. Download your maps before you head to the hills. When the clouds lower and you don't want to believe your compass bearing, this gives a five star confidence boost.

I have been using it several years ago for navigation on Iceland with preloaded maps. It was slow. It was 1 core tablet. Now I use it on 4 core mobile and it is same slow. It is ok until trace logs begins. Without logging it is not fast but ok. With logging it is not usable. Responses after several seconds. I have to start using pathaway even it has no option for more online maps.
replyContent: I am sorry to hear that and will work with you to diagnose it if desired and you contact us at the HelpDesk.

content: Navigation, GPS and map tools

I downloaded the CalTopo map and then selected areas of the Sierras that I plan to hike in this summer and then saved them. It's a little tricky trying to find the maps that I've named and stored, but I've been able to figure it out. I studied my saved maps and then created waypoints. Thereafter, I went to Whitney Portal and hiked to Lone Pine Lake. I shut off my data and put the phone in airplane mode, then opened the app and my saved map. I was able to pinpoint my location on the trail, worked perfectly!

I used the free version last weekend on a trip to Missouri Lakes trail in CO. I downloaded an area map section (tiles) so that I could use my phone as a GPS while out of cellphone service area. The app works fantastic. I turned airplane mode on and gps on. The app sips battery while in use, though of course uses more than airplane mode. However, I turned off location/GPS whenever I was not using the app. Very accurate in following the downloaded offline topo maps. It's great to have track info on the device so I can see distance traveled, altitude profile, etc.  I've gone ahead and purchased the Pro version because I was so impressed compared to my older dedicated GPS device, a Delorme PN-40. It's the most I've ever paid for an app, but it's literally worth more than my old $350 Delorme. That screen was always annoyingly small and my eyes are not getting any better. This $12 app does everything and more that the Delorme device did. And more. Super simple to download mostly free open source or government (USGS etc) map downloads for US. Not sure about other countries.
Shouldn't your screen be as clear as maps or Google earth? Mine and a buddy of mine are the same. Blurry!!
replyContent: Could you please write in and tell us What Map Source? What location? What are the numbers on the right? We do not ever claim that we will be exactly like Google Earth, but we would like to help you make it work for your activity.

content: I have been testing this extensively in a variety of New Mexico and colorado wilderness. It is a fantastic tool. I carry my phone as a camera might as well double its utility. Since discovering this app i have not used my handheld gps. Can get about 3 days on a charge. Then swap batteries or pull out the solar charger for those multi day trips.
I can take a bearing and use a map and compass, but BackCountry Navigator puts my dot on the map and keeps all kinds of stats. I don't go out without caching maps and charging up!
Great for backpacking!
Just awesome.

Outstanding resource! I have used this App as a backup to a map and compass for a few years now and have been delighted with its accuracy and reliability. In airplane mode, the phone battery lasts all day and with a robust cover is the equal to my Garmin GPS. The topo and aerial coverage of New Zealand is excellent. The app is stable and has not let me down during daily use on a bush project these past two months. Is there any way of incorporating true (topo) surface area estimates? Many thanks.
Used to use Locus maps, until the OS map tweak for the UK stopped working. This app still has access to OS maps, so it's my new favourite.
I had image handling errors covering the larger portion of my maps... I could zoom in and out and different spots would give this fault.
replyContent: Perhaps we can help if you write in with the location and the map source.

content: I use this for work several days a week, after switching from another app because of stability issues in that app. Backcountry Navigator (Demo or Pro) has none of the stability issues that the other app had. It has a few bells and whistles that were absent in the other app, too, like better collecting and storage of related data into "trip databases".

Absolutely love this app!  The ability to download maps in advance really puts it over the top.  Use it for hiking, boating, geocaching. The flexibility to choose different map sources as the need arises just increases it's worth for me.  I'd estimate I use this multiple times a week.
Latest update made the app unusable. Not worth buying.
replyContent:
I see. Please be in touch with the Helpdesk about your complaint. 
There were no big changes in the last update.

content: Very good topo app for hiking. Bit of a learning curve but it's logical. Caltopo and US Forest Service maps are detailed and allow for plenty of zoom. Using this on a tablet to scope out a route, phone screen is too small to see much overview for planning purposes, but phone is much better for on location route finding, track recording. So it would be much better to have a cloud sync rather than have to import and export gpx files.

I bought the map for Alaska and it doesn't really show the maps where I'm at and can I get my refund back in my account,I bought the back country pro and The Alaska map. :( when is the next update for my app for Alaska??? It still says no map coverage!
replyContent: We gave you two options for your area in response to your query at the HelpDesk. Please respond there.

content: Ive used this app for about a year now when going off roading on my motorcycle. Not only can I plan where I want to go but I can see what tracks & trails I've done before! It's replaced my need for a stand alone GPS unit.

Great app and I use it regularly when hunting on 1800 acre ranch. The cache feature is highly recommended and very useful when entering areas with scarce to no cell coverage. Multi hour or all day use especially when recording tracks is a battery drain. This is more the result of phone using more resources for GPS and map updating than the actual app itself. When no cell coverage or poor coverage is available turn phone to Airplane mode and use cached maps. You will get much better battery life. Be prepared and have a reliable source to charge your phone. Like most things a little planning ahead will make your experience with the app much better!
The fog was as thick as soup.  This app got me to my blind, safe and sound
This app keeps getting better and better.
I use this when I'm out prospecting and metal detecting. Developer is super fast to fix any problems and keep this software at the top of the game.  Highly recommended!

the top "my location" menu button always stops working after some time. I would actually prefer to have a recording/pause button on screen without the need to go into this menu every time to pause or start track recording. Especially when you can not get into the menu to unpause... otherwise works ok, compass is a bit glitchy on my xperia z3 but I dont really use it... Would be great if you could continue a previously recorded track.
