replyContent: The menu is a standard Android menu and not meant to stop working after any particular time. Be in touch with us at the helpdesk about the behavior you are seeing.

content: Compass is pretty much never right. Very long lag to find position. Galaxy S6
replyContent: We don't have full control over the compass sensor or GPS fix  time of hardware.

content: Outback gps app is not clear when zoomed in.
replyContent: Contact us through the helpdesk, and we may be able to help you.

content: Awesome hiking, camping, fishing, and particularly hunting app.

Love the app... takes a little bit of effort to learn how to use it but they keep making it easier with each update.  I use in the trail and on the backroads leading there as cell service is often unavailable.
Best
I love this app for its abilities. Download of topo maps make this an instant win for me. It's the only one I have that consistently works.
installed on lollipop.. mucked my sd card permissions and now cannot store anything on sd card
replyContent: Apps do not have the ability to muck with any sd card permissions. Contact Android or your manufacturer.

content: This app, used with my Galaxy S5, continues to work very well, as a 'back-up' GPS mapping tool, for my Garmin 800, whilst cycling.  There certainly is a learning curve for this app, but it's not difficult to use.  I frequently cycle where there is zero cell coverage, so have downloaded considerable map tiles from Open Cycle Maps (free), which is one of the vast array of map sets available  in the app.   The OCM maps contain a very decent coverage of area trails, which is highly useful.

I use this app daily for work and play.  Installed this on my phone and Android radio in my truck and love the ability to see exactly where I am.  I spend a lot of time off roads, and this is the only GPS app I have found that works for everything I need.
Get app to take in the back country. I took back my top of the line gps after using this app.... Awesome. Thanks
Not relevant for Africa as it has no maps for the region.
replyContent: Not true. Africa is part of the world and therefore covered by worldwide maps such as OpenCycleMaps. Even better, you can download country wide maps from here using instructions at the helpdesk. http://www.openandromaps.org/en/downloads/africa

content: I love this app, use it all the time hunting, camping, and hiking
replyContent: Glad to see it used

content: Excellent app,  not simple to use,  but walks you through. Great to have in your pocket for deep woods hikes.  This app has saved me on more that one occasion. Worth the price when compared to a dedicated handheld GPS receiver.

I rarely pay for apps. I paid more than I ever have for this one only to find it wants you to pay even more for decent maps. It is also very difficult to get the hang of. I have attempted to use it 4wheeling a dozen times. Been happy with it twice. Great for people with more money than me who are also very tech savy. Mostly I find it frustrating. Still trying to learn it 2 years later, so I can feel like these other 5 star reviewers.
replyContent: Please contact the helpdesk if you'd like to talk about a refund.

content: Really nice app! cache your destination area, and you will have a reference to most trails. Found myself using it to figure out distance, and at time, to get back to trail after going off course - without panic :) Kudos for not being a battery hog as well, will only use GPS when active!
Lots of features, but poor UI. Could use a serious overhaul on design and ease of use/navigation.
replyContent: Thank you for the feedback.

content: Works great on HTC one
replyContent: Glad it is working well.

content: Non of that Google maps rubbish

I tried a number of other GPS apps for Android before coming across this one.  The ability to download from various sources and countries is a big plus.  I also really like the trip histogram showing speed and altitude changes.
Been using this for several months now in the Tahoe area.  Very happy with it.
Awesome
Fantastic
Great app, super useful. I use it for navigation on forest service roads and ORV trails deep in the cascades. Saved my bacon more than once!

Love that you can search and find hikes and i am excited to use the android wear support. Hopefully they will take advantage of the ambient mode for android wear.  Update: Thanks for responding. Would be awesome if the ambient mode could have a black and white version of the map data. maybe just show the path and only update every minute or so. It would have to be optional as some watches can not handle this very well. But the LG G watch R, can handle full colour on the screen all day long as long as it's not solid white. I currently use IW weather radar as my main watch face and love the fact its always full colour.
replyContent: We do take advantage of it if you use the BackCountry Watch Face - that's the lowest power usage. We'll be able to do that in the app as well soon with some development updates.

content: Great for elk hunting around Colorado!
I use this Ap for backcountry Overland  travel and it has been fantastic.

I live in the mountains of Colorado. I use this app several times a week for skiing, hiking, climbing and fishing.  The ArcGIS map is wonderful because it shows timberline, avalanche paths, wetlands, cliffs and other obstacles which may impede cross country travel. I've tried several other topo apps, they don't come close and this one is always improving. Recently I tried Accu Terra maps for a trial period, it is up to date on trails but I don't understand why they don't show terrain features like ArcGIS.
Bought it Thursday and used it for an off road trip in the Sierra's the following Saturday and. easily became the best GPS I have owned.  Powerful and easy to use.  I will recommend to friends.
Used this for first time today on a hike. It worked great! Very nice app!

Best topo/outdoors GPS app for Android. As an iphone convert, I was searching for something to replace a very popular and awesome app that's exclusive to ios for some dumb reason. However, this app will suffice. It is a little bit more cumbersome but it is full of features.

Wish I could get a refund. Bloated, confusing. Takes hours to download sections of Australian maps which you have have to choose by drawing rectangles, does not work in offline mode, almost impossible to mark places for later use. Very disappointed. Save your money and use HERE, a GPS program included free in the Lollipop version of Android. Does everything I thought this program would do.
replyContent: It DOES work in offline mode. It is not impossible to mark places for later use. If you would like to talk about a refund then contact the helpdesk.

content: I've used this app several times over the past few years on multi-day backpacking hikes into the Grand Canyon. As long as I have in advance downloaded the relevant maps (for free) I have been able to see my actual location interposed onto the USGS maps (and terrain maps too). I used the app to mark and later to locate my water/food cache. I don't go off the grid without it!
One of the few apps worth paying for. Downloading maps allows you to put phone into airplane mode and still track you via gps navigation, thus conserving battery.
The maps in my area are good. The app work perfectly.
Replaced my $400 GPS and it does more!
I've been using this app for several years now, and although becoming more complex all the extras have made it a very usable program
Has all the features I was looking for.  Very relevant for orienteering or mission planning.  Quick and easy to pull up MGRS.  UI is good.
Works good, maps are excellent. Using it for trail riding and saved me a few times.
I try other similar apps when I feel like a change but this one always works brilliantly and still beats them all. Mountain biking with OS maps in the UK has never been easier!
Works like a champ with all the updates Android has been sending.

I have had this app for almost two years. I absolutly love it. I use it snowmobiling, fishing and driving the logging roads here in Maine. I recently used it out on the pond one foggy morning while fishing. We could not see anything so I pulled up this app and we were able to fish all morning without being able to see where we were. I cannot express how useful this app is to me. Thanks again!!!
Used it on several backpacking trips in Utah and Arizona. Who needs a handheld GPS device when you can use your phone and SEE where you are on a customized topo map?!
I thought the other app I used was the best.  Nope. This is far superior.  Thanks.

I've been enjoying this app for a long time. (Just a heads up for the developers, my security software is going crazy with that new permission with the camera) I remain happy with the app and wouldn't hesitate to use it. They have a good reputation for caring about their customers needs.

Have been using this App for many years with 3 or more different phones and a Nexus 7 tablet and have not had a problem that I could not resolve by reading the help or how to files.  Their web site and Facebook page are very good resources and the developer clearly knows his...ahh stuff. When out and away from it all I always have my compass, hard copies of maps and BackCountry Navigator in my hunting, fishing or hiking pack.

I've used this app for over a year now and although it takes a while to understand how to use it, it has a very rich set of features.  It has now almost completely replaced my dedicated  GPS for hiking.  Accuracy on phones keeps improving to the point they are typically as good as the dedicated units.  Love the map caching feature, as most places I hike have no cell service.  Highly recommended!!

I REALLY like this app, but the latest update gives them the ability to take pictures with your camera at any time without your knowledge. Though it's not as good, I'M DELETING THIS APP and going with Backpacker GPS Trails Pro. This is extremely disappointing!
replyContent: Really? The only time camera is used is if you push the camera button when recording a waypoint to take a picture for that waypoint. That's not in the background and is certainly not without your knowledge.

content: Not entirely intuitive, but it works very well. I've taken it camping, hiking fly fishing, backpacking, prospecting, shooting, 4wheeling, canoeing, and others; it hasn't missed a beat in Colorado. I do recommend buying the BLM upgrade (if they still charge for it) if you plan on shooting or worried about trespassing. Also, bring a ZipLock bag to waterproof your phone; leave some air in it to let it float if you are on deep water or push the air out so it sinks if you are wading. Mark you fishing holes.
Best outdoors App I have ever used
Easy and accurate for my back country prospecting trips.
Asus memo. Four wheelin all day, didn't miss a beat. Great, no, Awesome app.......
Gets me back to the truck everytime love the app
For real. I regret buying it. Very complicated and always asking for money.
replyContent: Contact us at the helpdesk if you would like to discuss that regret.

content: Probably the most useful app i have installed on my phone, and the BCN team have always responded to my queries. I have used the app widely in UK, France and Japan. Very convenient and saves buying expensive maps.  I have had some problems with storage - the maps can take up a lot of space, and if you have to change device, or just clear out space, you can lose maps. I recommend using the Named Map Folder facility and saving maps on an external device when you don't need them for a while.

No need to purchase an expensive hand held GPS when you purchase this app. This app executes everything that a GPS does, except there's no need to purchase those expensive topo maps/software.  With the ability to download map areas, phone battery life lasts for days in the woods on airplane mode. Excellent job!

Over recent years I have convinced several hikers in our tramping club to use your easy and accurate app for navigation and track recording. They now leave their expensive specific gps equipments at home, and use their android mobile phones for hiking gps. We also use Backcountry Navigator frequently when cycling in New Zealand. Great for back country tracks and also city cycle and walking tracks
Great!
Love it.  Really helps my experience in the out-of-doors.
The only issue I have ever had is with saving maps to SD card, and the SD card was at fault. Save smaller maps to your phone, and it will save you miles in the backcountry.
Give these people your money.
Customer support works hard to help your problems. Be patient, describe issues and communicate with them.
Don't leave home without it

Dunno what Eric Anderson's problem is (complaint May 4th). It's a great app and also incredibly good value. I ditched my new Garmin Oregon in favour of BackCountry Navigator loaded on my Samsung Galaxy S3 with waterproof cover. Can't speak highly enough of the app and I would have paid way more for it.
Great app. Usd it often in the Canadian Rockies and recently in the Grand Canyon. Like it because of the different maps that  can be used with great resolution.
Any updates would love to keep it
In combination with Cal-Topo, I was easily able to plan a route, download base-map and record my trail on the Colorado river in the Grand Canyon!  Talk about off-line wilderness.

Great App. I was looking at the hand held GPS units, but Back Country Navigator saved me a lot of money. The app works great in my local forest hikes. I will be trusting it in Canada this fall on a hunting trip.

Absolutely fantastic! This is my goto app when I want to follow a route on my bike. I prepare the route on a web based platform, send the GPX to my phone and install it to BCN. I love the Open Cycle maps. Thanks for this app. Every update improves it :) p.s. I'm sure Eric's a nice bloke but his comment makes him look a right nob ;)

I love Backcountry Navigator.  It has helped me not only in the mountains, but also on the freeway and even out of the country.  I use it mainly for backcountry skiing or hiking.  I plot my routes or points of interest in Google Earth and then email them to my phone and import them to BN.  I also do the reverse after a trip.  I often create way points at points of interest and create a track of exactly where I went.  No need for data or cell signal.  Just use your GPS and the maps you downloaded before you leave a cell signal.  I also put the phone into Airplane Mode to conserve the battery (I'm not going to get a signal in the wilderness anyways and the phone stops searching if it is in Airplane Mode).  I just recently used this for a trip to China.  It was not only fun to plot my hotels and points of interest before I left , but I used it a number of times to show someone where I wanted to go since I speak almost no Mandarin. It only failed me on the bullet trains  (I think the combination of the speed and the electric wires above the train would not allow me to lock onto the GPS satellites - this is my phones issue - not BN.    Great App!!!
Brilliant app

I wont A REFUND!! This App is worthless. Do I have to report you to Google to get a refund? I can not zoom in close. This app would be great if it would zoom in closer. Please tell me how to zoom in closer or I want a refund. The numbers on the side are 16:20.  Not to helpful if you cant see where you are at.
replyContent: Eric, it is not appropriate to complain about customer service if you have never contacted them. If you would like a refund email support@crittermap.zendesk.com. Mention your Google Order number or gmail address because they need that to grant a refund.

content: Small screen use with topo maps is challenging.
Latest update fixed scrolling issue on my 1st gen MotoX.

Out of all the applications I've purchased on my phone over the last 4 years, this has proven to be the most useful. I use it every time I go hiking. The recent addition of Google Wear functionality makes this a killer app for any outdoorsman who appreciates technology.

THIS WORKS WITHOUT CELL SERVICE!!  Love it!! Way better than paying hundreds for a garmin! Better maps than garmin! Update: Been using this for 5 yrs snowmobiling and atv'ing. Garmin doesn't want you to know about this. Turns your android into a full  featured topo mapping gps. Works without cell service and just sips battery power. Great deal at 10x the price. I'm running this on an s3 and samsung tab s, Works great on both.  THANK YOU  Crittermap!
Quit possibly the best hiking app for my phone.
Amazing use of topos.  Used backpacking and never drained battery or missed a beat.
Best $13 I ever spent !!!!
I have a $400 topo GPS that has less capability than this app. When you live in the back country this app comes in very handy. Never have I felt as confident to explore!

I have used this app for a couple of years now and, as a mapping professional, I find it to be just about spot-on. It does exactly what CritterMap claims and works on every Android platform I have ever put it on. The ability to export tracks and points to GPX or KML is another great feature if you want to view your trips in Google Earth or another GIS platform such as ArcGIS.
Great app, used it tons of times while camping and backpacking. Its had some glitches for me in the past. It also really needs Pebble support!

I have been using this app for a few years now and I have to say that it has only gotten better over that time. Absolutely amazing. I use this on my motorcycle as a GPS/Nav unit. Works great for adventure touring, you can download the maps you need before leaving home. Thus making it work without cell service. Used it on the COBDR.
While zooming or scrolling app locks up only way out of it is by pulling the battery. Horrible.
replyContent: Sorry to hear that. Be sure and be in touch at our helpdesk if you haven't already to hear about our latest theory.

content: I've tried for 2 years to get the hang of this. I can usually sort out technology if I sit down for an hour and go through it carefully. Not this one. My wife hates it when we hike and I try using it because I howl with frustration. But I'll keep trying because so many others rave about it, and because its now a challenge.
replyContent: I see. How about contact us at the helpdesk and tell us what we can do so it will finally make sense. Then it can be a challenge for us.

content: I use this map for walking and climbing (always with a paper map backup) and it's always been fantastic glad to see the UK maps are working again I didn't realise how much I used it until they stopped working

Great Comms from Nathan and Dan after the hiatus caused by Bing Maps resulting in UK OS Maps not working. (Not BCN's Fault)...solution:  Choose "Select Areas for Download", mark an area and instead of choosing "Download", choose Menu->Delete. Go to the file system, and delete the folder mmosxp underneath bcnav/tiles.   Since the 5.7.3 update and the clean up:The App is working perfectly, hope it continues. Best App for hiking in the UK, so I am really pleased with the outcome
Great app for mapping your favorite unmapped trails and back roads. Love it!
Has (for a cost) hunting unit boundaries and land ownership maps that overlay

The best walking and research mapping app for the UK. Superb detail from OS Explorer maps - by far the best maps in any app. EDIT: v5.7.3 has got UK OS Maps working again - great work from the developers. Without these maps, the app would be useless in the UK.
replyContent: Christopher, we have found solutions. See the topic on the helpdesk to recover.

content: Great app
Been using a long time...  Update..  Still awesome.

I'm very happy and relieved to update that OS map functionality for the whole UK seems to be returning after a two week break in the service. The ability to use OS maps with GPS on my phone for the whole UK easily makes this a 5 star app and a worthwhile investment of £12 for the full version (it's the price of just two OS paper maps when the app provides OS maps for the whole UK!). The customer service from the developer also seems very good with responses to queries on the website, and I was offered a full refund if the OS functionality didn't return soon enough for me which I was impressed by. I'm so relieved that the OS maps have returned as I love using this app to find my way when out on walks and record my trips and see the associated stats etc. Excellent!
replyContent: Glad that it is working for you.

content: I load GPS coordinates for hiking and it works perfectly. I've never had any problems with it.
Great app and has been used in real life death situation. It worked perfectly in a white out.

I had trouble with installation of this app and wrote the review below but finally got it working I think.  The problem I was facing I think arose because I was installing the Pro version while the Demo was still installed.  I think that must have broken everything.   After multiple attempts at installation, I realized that the demo version no longer worked and made the connection, uninstalled it and then reinstalled the pro.  Now everything seems to be working fine although I haven't really had a chance to use it that much.   Perhaps a note on the installation would be good to let people know that they should remove the demo before making this installation.   Can't wait to use it!  -------------------------------  I love the free version and was excited to buy the pro but it was a mess.  The installation was very slow and stuck at around 83% twice.  Yes, I installed it twice because when I tried to finally open it, I only got a black screen.  I use the free version with relatively few problems (there are glitches) and was hoping this would be better but just the opposite.  I can't even get it to open.   good luck with the App.  I hope to be able to use it soon.
replyContent: We do not control installation - Google does. But we are in touch with you through the helpdesk to try and figure it out.

content: Grea app

Sigh.. Had to uninstall and reinstall. Turns out if you move the app to your SD after opening it, then it no longer finds the original maps it was loading. (That figured out, I increased my rating)  Downloaded some KMZ and GPX map files for the trip I had planned. Once those were imported it worked great.   Initially I had problems but after a little tinkering it all worked out. Upped to 4 stars. Not 5 because of initial issues.  After all that I found that due to the way backcountry navigator stores its files I could not use storage cleaning software. I used 360 security and the storage cleaning ruined back country requiring me to uninstall and reinstall again. sigh..getting tired of having to reinstall after getting all my waypoints in.
Not good without Internet connection if u live in quebec / canada
replyContent: Not true. If you don't think that is working, talk to the helpdesk. Some issues were resolved recently with Canadia servers.

content: All topo maps for practicallt whole world
Excellent app, works great on Sony Xperia Z3 Tablet Compact...
Paid version. Prior versions worked well. Now I cannot download tiles. It stalls after 20% or so completion.  Galaxy S4 storage on SD card. Uninstalled the app.
replyContent: Storage gotten full? Recent update to Android 4.4? Check with the helpdesk and we may be able to help you.

content: The cream of the crop for backcountry navigation. Excellent map selection, and the ability to cache for offline use is extremely useful.
A great app

Great app, I use this in my tuck 4 wheeling on the trails all over California. Let's me see what's around me and what's coming up. Very useful especially if your not familiar with the trail. Would have given 5 stars but there are so many features it takes several uses to figure out.
Best gps out. Love it. Use it motorbike riding in nsw sydney. If you have any issues you email them and they sort you out strait away. Very happy
Really well done

Why all the five star ratings? Everybody but me understand this program?  You got to what download MAPs after buying this but what ? Canada Base. Canada Toporama, NR Canada Topo ?  What is the difference? I am supposed to know what they do?  Say you want a Map of  a Provincial Park  you supposed to draw a square around the park and download it? Using Canada Base. Canada Toporama, NR Canada Topo ? What happens you forget?  The addons seem to be American only, useless in Canada. I am open minded maybe they tell me how to use this app and they maybe I can increase the rating. Ok they pointed me to web site with instruction not ideal .... but it works
replyContent: Yes, you do draw a square around the park and download it. You are welcome to try all the maps and see the difference for yourself. Or tell us at the HelpDesk which choices you don't want and check the help on how to use the app while you are there.

content: I use to use Memory-Map Navigator with Windows Phone, because I  bought it before BCN was created. I switched to BCN when I moved to Android, because MMN was not available on Android. When MMN finally had an Android version, I tried it out, but switched back to BCN. BCN is easier to use. I believe BCN has matured and MMN has not kept up.

Been using this app for several years now. I love it! I have the paid version as well as a few layers. Absolutely love this app. It is a Lil confusing at first but once you get it and understand all the features, its amazing.
Used on many global bike packing trips. There's a learning curve, but I think this is mostly a mental model about how it works thing. Hasn't let me down, has got me where I needed to go.

Really engineered for serious hiking nav. They were quick to develop an app for my Gear 2 wearable. I wish there were more maps available for Canada and Europe, but that has nothing to do with the developers. Good work!
Best. App. Ever.

I've used Backcountry Navigator for over 4 years now. It works great and just keeps getting better. I particularly like using the "World Open Cycle Maps".  They have very accurate hiking trail information as well as bike routes and trails.  It's easy to download large areas of detailed maps.
love this app
The shiz
Once you get in you have to start buying other maps. Thought when you paid the $ 11.99 you were getting ever setting you needed. Don't let them sucker you in.
replyContent:
That is absolutely *not true*. You do not have to buy other maps.
The majority of maps have no additional cost. There's is only one(1) map that requires a subscription. That is clearly mentioned in the description. If you would like more clarification, then please contact the HelpDesk.

content: This is a fantastic and feature-filled app for loading maps and managing GPS tasks, but unfortunately it often stops tracking after an hour or two for no apparent reason. I've had the same problem on two different devices now. It seems to work as long as you don't make the app run in the background, but try multitasking, say to take some pictures, and chances are it will crash. If dependable tracking isn't important it's a great app.
Revolutionizing GPS. Look out Garmin and Magellan. This app is the solution to all trail needs!
Would be perfect if it had AZ. Game Units.

This app the ultimate! A big thanks to the BCN team & LG for resolving the issue I had with my LG phone. Etc. Now I can go back to using the best GPS/ Topo map app available bug free on my power efficient LG smart phone. Awsum thanks peoples!
Ratings
This is a truly amazing app. Easy to use once you follow the tutorial and renders all other gps apps obsolete.  Buy it and support the hard working people who make it happen!
Works splendid

I'd been thinking of switching to iPhone but I got Nathan's newsletter today and, you know, I don't want to give up BackCountry Navigator or Nathan's newsletters so now I've just got to find a new Android phone with a decent GPS and good battery life.

I use this app on a Nexus 7 tablet to scout potential hiking trail routes. I can import gpx files with tracks of property boundaries, existing trails, and my planned route, and I can see them all at once in different colors on a high-resolution topo map. As I hike I can record tracks and waypoints, and then export them to use in my desktop mapping software. This has worked out a lot better for me than my old, hand-held gps. The user forum on the CritterMap website is also helpful in guiding me to features that I didn't know about. The more I use this app, the more impressed I am with what it can do.

I downloaded to phone the entire 12A game unit in Arizona and during my adventure, found myself putting my Garmin Oregon away and using my Note 3. There is next to zero cell reception there but with the maps downloaded and GPS on, it was next to perfect. I just need to find out how to get the Forest Service roads on it and it'll be perfect.
replyContent: Try the Forest Service 2013 maps.

content: I was considering a handheld GPS for hiking, but heard about this on a youtube video. Man am I glad I tried this first! Great for hiking, boating, etc. Only knock is no GSMNP trail map. Please add that!
Love the app

I am an outfitter and in the field 300 days a year. The best part of this app is that you can download maps before you go out into the field, which makes it possible to use your device as a comprehensive GPS without cell coverage.

It doesn't sound like the Critter Map will update and include NZTM2000....  Sorry guys but after paying out for the pro version it just didn't work well enough to be safe..... so I've switched to another app called New Zealand Topo Maps Pro by ATLOGIS Geoinformatics.   This has all the same features at BCN but supports NZTM2000. UI is actually easier to use too.
Wipes out saved maps after updates.
replyContent: BCN certainly does not wipe out saved maps after updates. If you think it has, you are welcome to contact the helpdesk.

content: Best backpacking and hiking topo app I've used ever. Been using it for all my trips for 3 years now :-)
I pre-download the area I'm going to, turn on airplane mode, and hike with a great map/GPS. Has worked perfectly every time.

A must get for anybody outdoors. I use it for hiking and geocaching. Yes it uses alot of battery but I bought a large external battery. With the cost of that and the app it is still way cheaper then store bought GPS units
The app is glitchy on my phone and doesn't do half the stuff the tutorial says it does. Not happy.
replyContent: I am sorry to hear that it hasn't worked well for you. Please contact the HelpDesk for diagnosis or a refund.

content: A great example of tools available in our modern day society. Have had the app for a few weeks and have tested the download area for some very remote locations far away from any cell towers.I was able to navigate the back country roads with great confidence.  This app is an outdoor enthusiasts  dream come true.

We just returned from 5 weeks in southern Mexico, driving more than 5,000 km.  We used Back Country Navigator and Google GPS Navigator every day.  Each day, while connected with Wi-Fi or 3G, I would get Google Navigator oriented with the driving route for the day's travel AND down load the route and map of the next town's details in Back Country Navigator.  Between the two programs, we were able to find destinations easily and, with Back Country's great detail, we could usually see what hotels and restaurants were within walking distance of where we landed, usually working out from the central plaza.  We also, of course, were able to use Back Country Navigator's down loaded maps of Mexican mountain trails for our daily hikes.  Couldn't be more happy with the program! Dick Devin Boulder, Colorado

If you're looking for something with 3 buttons that you can learn in 30 seconds, keep looking, but if you want an app packed with features that will do just about anything you need a GPS app to do, this is it.  I don't buy a lot of apps, I use mainly the free versions, but this one I paid for the PRO version and it's been worth every penny.  Take the time to learn how to use it and you won't be disappointed.  Would love to see a toggle on the mainscreen to switch between sat/aerial view and topo view.  Maybe it's there and I haven't found it yet.
Turn your phone into a true outdoor activity GPS. Waypoints, tracks, and download satellite and topo maps and save to phone so you can use it with no cell service.

I use BCN for all navigation now. Only issue is the app crashes play store when updating but it updates with a few tries so no big deal. It is perfect for fishing and/or exploring the back country with no signal. I am yet to use all the features and am always very pleasantly surprised that the app has exactly what I need already installed. Best app on my phone.
I love this app and use it all the time. PLEASE GET COLORADO LAKES TOPO overlay!
Fantastic value for money. I use it all the time.

I give it a 5 for its overwhelming content, but I'm knocking off a point because "I think" the user interface is frustrating. Probably just me! I bought the pro version because I believe in the app, but I also bought iBird pro and find it to be a frustrating app to navigate. The BCN developer is lightning fast to answer any questions, so you've got nothing to lose.  Could be a 5* for you.  Thanks
replyContent: Write in, please.

content: Fantastic app.  Used this extensively with a Galaxy 4s on a recent cycle tour through the Middle East and Eastern Europe. I used it with OpenCycleMap - great detail all the way from Iran through Turkey and all the way through to Europe. I downloaded maps when wifi was available - usually several days at a time. I found OpenCycleMaps, used in conjunction with Google Maps great for finding my way into European cities via bike routes. I must admit that I find the UI a bit un-intuitive, (is that just me?).  Having learned my way around it fairly well, I find that if I don't use it for a few weeks, I have to re-learn many of the functions.  Good support from the developer.

My wife & I recently took part in a charity Raid (an off-road race) in Morocco  on the western edge of the Sahara Desert - the Maroc Callenge. We were issued GPX tracks which had to be followed for each stage. These tracks were duly entered into our Garmin GPS etrex units and our Samsung tablet. Because of the incompetence of the organisers the tracks issued had too many waypoints for the Garmin units and duly failed in the middle of a desert track. Without our Samsung and BCN we would have been totally lost. As it was we were placed 8th in our group. Thanks BCN
Does everything I want a gps app to do and then some and does it all flawlessly. S5 Active

Works great when you have gps line of sight in good weather.  I download the maps and they are on my phone before the trip.  I have maps even without cell phone service.  Great app.    UPDATE:  I have now used this app on numerous trails and both Galaxy S4 & S5 phones.   This app is great!   Satellite connection for gps work's in all but the most foul weather.   The map downloads are great and easy too.
Great app used it for years one of the best. 😊

I use it for snowmobiling.  It tracks well in the mountains and I like that I can overlay my route on satellite images.  The track graphs give a great summary of an area for future reference.  Come on cell phone manufacturers, keep working on the battery life issue.
Now, if they would only make a phone battery that could last as long as a dedicated GPS.
Fantastic hiking app
Used this to find a couple waterfalls I had the coordinates to. Recorded a track that gave me some really great stats on my hike.
Download variety of topics maps to your phone and don't depend on data connection. Works on all your devices. Using it for couple years now for off road navigation.
Love this for camping

There are other GPS map apps. I have deleted them in favor of  BCN. I have also discovered that leaving BCN on while driving can help to discover new places to hike or hunt I otherwise would not have noticed.  This is a great GPS .
Awesome.
Absolutely love this app, my favorite, and better than all the expensive standalone GPS units I own.
Once you learn how to use it you will love it. Nothing better even close to this price. Reliable, easy to use, free updates, download and upload ability. Just awesome.
Excellent navigational application, use it for hunting and other outdoor activities.
Only wish it would run with Google Earth as its map
replyContent: Get us Google Earth's permission, and we'll make it happen.

content: Best navigation map out there, developer is super responsive, free map caching, all the features.

I have been using Backcountry Navigator for hiking and biking, however, I just pressed it into another sport - skiing.  We were up in Steamboat for the past few days and I thought I would start recording a track for the entire day.  At the end of the day I had a complete trail map of everything we skied including all of the stats.  I didn't pause when riding the lifts, but could have also done that so as not to have added in their data.  I will also use it during my AT ski trips this year. Samsung Galaxy S5

I use this app just about every time I go backpacking to verify I am where I think I am on my trail map. It has been especially handy when I travel in the desert where everything can sometimes look the same. I would love to see this app develop Android wear support.

This is an excellent app. I've used it as an aid to both walking and cycling. It's great on the tablet as a good sized OS map alongside a paper map. It's also useful in the car with the range of scales available. Good effort!
Didnt work off the grid.
replyContent: It most definitely does work off the grid. If you don't think it did, please check with the helpdesk.

content: Works very well.  Adds to my confidence when I'm in the wilderness because I always know where I am.   I was considering buying a dedicated hiking GPS device but tried this first.  Backcountry Navigator Pro suits my needs perfectly.   I only had one issue involving the Accuterra maps.  I sent an email to the developer and received a response from Nathan within the hour.  Btw the problem cleared up that day.  Highly recommend.

It's been a few years now and I've had many good times that Backcountry Navigator helped make even better! I love this app, and I'm purchasing an Android Wear Watch today so hope to see more progress in that direction. There is only one location I've visited that I couldn't find a map for, and that's Attu, the Westernmost point of North America in the Aleutian Islands.  5 stars and cheers to Backcountry Navigator!

Great app with the best support I've seen for any app. Avid outdoorsman so I'm always using maps and GPS.   I went from Android to iPhone and back to Android and this app was one of the reasons. Unfortunately you have to pay for more maps than before but that's not the fault of the app developer. You get what you pay for these days.
Used to be my favorite,  but map dowloads have gotten sow if the even download at all.  Gaia is faster, better user interface, and has worked every time
replyContent:
Could you please talk to us at the HelpDesk about what downloads have slowed? 
The map source and location matters.

content: Constantly working on updates! Always new features! Its no doubt the best land navagtion app out there!!  8 yr US Army Combat Infantryman.
Use it to track route when 4 wheeling. Lots of features. Wish it had more color features for tracking. Never have lost sat with moto Max.
replyContent: It does have color options for tracking.

content: It's no Garmin, but this is just my phone! Well worth the cost. Accuracy of tracks and logging has improved with updates. Thanks! Galaxy S3

I've used it in the back woods of Montana many times and find this app well worth it. Saves me $300 from having to buy a separate hand held GPS. Easy to use. But you have to load the area your going into before you get there so be sure to check your map range at different zoom levels before you are in the middle of someplace and don't get service to load the map.

I have used this now for about 2 years and love it. I have been tracking all my horseback riding miles on this app. I logged over 500 miles on this app in 2014 and have a record now of all my adventures. I love that it gives you the elevation changes, speed, moving time.etc. I have had a lot of my riding partners also buy this app and they are loving it too.
Has a few bugs with background maps not loading but overall very useful! Wish I could use Google as background map.
replyContent: What background maps aren't loading? Please contact the helpdesk. Google does not allow offline saving of its maps.

content: I've used this for a few years now to navigate the logging and gas roads in the rural area where I grew up for ATV riding and camping trips. The software does have a slight learning curve, but is extremely helpful once you have it figured out.
Shaded topos are easy to read

This program is awesome, very easy to use and works in my opinion much better than a buddies hi end gps unit. I have now mapped trails that I ride my quad on in the local area. Nicholai and Browns camp. Exported them and now buddies can use them even on garmin and other units. I really recommend trying this app before you go and spend a fortune on another unit you probably won't ever use or need. Thank you for such an awesome program. 1-10-15, The continual updates just keep making this better.

I've used 5 different map/GPS utilities.   This one seems to provide the best of online and offline navigating.   Heck,  you can even make your own maps.   I started using this a long time ago for geocaching.   Since then the developers keep adding capabilities, so now I use it for just about everything.   I especially like the offline map capability, since I like to hike in areas with little/no cell coverage.    This is the tool for me and I believe you will find it also does most everything for you.

I have used this app for canoeing and hiking in Northern Minnesota. I will Duluth Trading Company use a map and compass as my primary navigational tool, but this app (with previously downloaded maps & waypoints) on my Samsung Galaxy S5 saves time when looking for a canoe portage or a trail through sections of blowdown. I have used both a solar charger and a battery pack to keep my phone juiced.
This has replaced having OS maps other than as a backup in case phone dies.

Put this app on a 8.4" Samsung tablet that will fit in your back pocket while hiking and you have a combination that is far better than any $500 GPS unit. AccuTerra maps are elegant and well worth extra cost. Love the app.

Been using this app for a several years now, by far the most capable app of its kind on Google Play. I use it every year for hunting and whenever I go hiking to plot and track my route. Love that I can download the maps for use off-grid, love the detail in showing trails and landmarks, aerial imagery and topo is also very helpful. Well worth the purchase.

Used this in the Alpine mountains on my Galaxy Nexus. Downloaded offline maps and was able to follow trails and mark locations efficiently.  Used it for the entire 3 day backpacking trip into The Enchantments as a standalone GPS in airplane mode.  I had solar panels that kept it charged.  Was extremely accurate and useful.
I love the app.  The news letter rocks!  It keeps you informed on current & future enhancements.
Don't leave home without it!
Works great.
I had no idea an app like this existed. So far its better than any of my standalone GPS units!
Aawesome app. Worth every dime and penny. I use this on a daily bases and its a time saver. I used to carry my paper maps around now they stay in the truck. This on a 12" tablet and the best.
Great for hiking
Great job BCN folks, exactly what atv riders were looking for!
Works great on a snowmobile.
Using the app on a Samsung s5 active and nothing else I have used even comes close.  Best gps app, period.

Storage changes on android 4.4 mean that external storage (sd card) is unusable so I'm currently stuck in the position of having a Samsung s5 and needing a map pack that's larger than the storage I have available on the device - but I've got 55GB of storage sitting there unused on my sd card. The developers know about it and it's not their fault, it's just not really usable on android 4.4, maybe something will change on a later release - I hope it does because in my limited usage the app was excellent.
replyContent: It is inappropriate to say we are unusable on 4.4. See topic at length at http://support.crittermap.com/entries/27671140-Samsung-Devices-External-Storage-locked-after-4-4-updates- You CAN use your storage but you MUST use the directory setting which we will suggest in Root storage settings and you MUST back it up if you plan to uninstall us.

content: This app works awesome! Well worth the $

After a year of use this has been the most reliable GPS I've ever used.  I've used this backpacking in the Colorado mountains all year.  So easy to learn.  Great interface.  Customer service is swift and personal and work with you on a one on one level.  Great folks.
replyContent: Glad to hear it is working well in the Colorado Mountains.

content: In a nutshell, the best $10 ever spent!  I've been using this app for 3 years (+/-) to find maps for, and to track, my MTB, hiking and enduro MC outings. I have access to map layers suitable for every land management agency, and CritterMaps provides regular updates to keep the app working as advertised. I regularly use BCN outside 4G coverage with no problem... just be sure to download the map tiles you need first!
not working right.  Dev: please see my post on your Forum.
replyContent: The post has been seen. Pause/Continue is intended for rest stops. Using Stop then Start is more appropriate for the scenario you describe where you want to create two separate paths.

content: Had some issues in previous versions with Samsung Galaxy Note 3,  those have been promptly resolved. Thanks for a great program and excellent support!
With a waterproof case, I'm confident in heading out in the woods for a day or two with this app.
Great app with most of the features but without the $$$ of standalone higher than entry level GPS units.
Been using it for a couple years. Never had an issue
One of the best
Indispensable when out of tower range
Have problems with Samsung older phone. Not enough storage, even though I have a s.d. card installed that not recognized.
Sign up to their newsletter too. It's not spam but very informative.
I use the app regularly for work.  I work as a game warden and use this for marking sites of interest. Very reliable.
Great program!
I use this on a Nexus 7 when I hike,  and I get Topo maps of all the  places, presented in outstanding detail. Highly recommended.
Awesomeness, used it all over the world and it kicks butt!
Excellent

I've been using this app since 2011. I find this app always evolving and changing for the better. This app replaces the need for an expensive GPS. It does everything! I definitely recommend it to any outdoorsy person. This app is not really designed for GPS beginners, but it is becoming more user friendly as time goes on.
Great app for hunting!
Great app, only one I've ever spent money on, and I don't regret it. Great for the Colorado outdoors as well as foreign countries with no internet phone service.
Awesome

We have been using the Pro version for over a  2 1/2years now for our backcountry horse rides.  Downloading huge sections of topos allows us the confidence to bushwack off the trails in the forests and deserts of Nev, Ca, Ut, & Co.  Saving the tracks allows us to share them with other people and be able to take the same routes again in the future.  If more people would take the time to learn how to download topos and work the software there would be fewer dissatisfied people! Great job Nathan & staff B&A
I love bugs bunny!!
This app is constantly evolving into the greatest map source, using consumer input every step of the way. As for those whom don't "Get It?", let's not ask the developer to make a icon for everything.

I can't imagine not having this tool when out walking now.  The OS maps are great and offline download are the key features for me.  Interface could be better but once your up and running its a non issue.  Great value.
Best App around for wilderness trampers.These guys are responsive and really work at making their app the best .

I installed this app by a recommendation from a friend. Not expecting much more than a simple navigation app, I am extremely impressed after using it. I upgraded to the pro version and it's worth every penny. I rarely use a gps device to navigate from my experiences using a Gamin 62ST, which i sold. I'm more of a map and compass kind of guy. The reason I love this app so much is because it's powerful. It does everything the Garmin did and ties all that into my phone.

Used the pro version on my first ever elk hunt here in Az. Briefly ease of use and level of detail on the map feature made it a successful  hunt in one of the remote wilderness areas..tanks and trails were clearly marked and accurately tracked all convienently stored on my android phone....super app.love it and have recommended  it to my friends. Thanks
Older version was awesome, black screen/ not responding/ force close..with update,even after complete re-install..Casio  GzOne
replyContent: Please be in touch at the helpdesk. Most likely there are some memory limitations.

content: Over the 4 or 5 years I've been using this app it's seen big improvements.    I find it very useful. Love the new help features.  Thanks for keeping the improvements coming.
Works very well
Thanks for updating to the new style Android menu interface. I've used this for several years and you have always updated consistently. A way to back up way points online would be a great addition.

I like this app and have used it on multiple excursions. What would make it even better is if you could overlay multiple maps. I also use "Offline Maps" and find this feature useful for highlighting multiple features that are not available on a single map download. Keep up the good work.
Nice this app is now starting to support sea charts. Functionality is top rate.
Using every time when out of pavement
Best app I have ever used. Have not used a regular GPS since I got the app and I have been all over the woods and hills on several trips.

I purchased this app for my first elk hunting trip after testing the trial version and learning how to work it. This has just about every feature you could need in a GPS. The offline maps are actually quite small on file size. Would like to see waypoint-to-waypoint track generation and database transfer ability between devices, but not a requirement.

I feel like a beta tester trying to use this app with the accuterra subscription. In order to get the huge accuterra maps on your removable drive you must root your android phone and fix a script file. I tried the B.C.N workaround to this issue but the downloaded accuterra maps were corrupt. (It takes MANY HOURS to download accuterra maps). I rooted my phone and gave back country navigator root access and spent 5 days trying to get a functional database on the removable drive to no avail.
replyContent: It is *not* true that people have to root to use Accuterra maps, and we do *not*recommend it.

content: Compass no longer works after update. Uninstalled and reinstalled but it didn't fix the issue.
replyContent: Sorry to hear that, but we have tested on several Nexus 5s and found the compass to be working just fine. You are welcome to write in and try and troubleshoot the problem.

content: Used it on TMB, Hadrian's wall, various hikes in Hudson Valley. Has all the essential features for long distance hikes. Great integration with everytrail website. Works great with Samsung device and LG g2. Testing it on Sony Xperia now.

I have a Polaris RZR 800S and we go out in the boondocks alot and need a premimum GPS and ToPo in order to navagate our way around and get back to the truck safetly,...this app works for us and I recomend it to others.

Backcountry navigator is the most important app on my tab3. I use it with offline maps for fishing and tramping (hiking) in New Zealand. A cool thing you can't do with a paper map- make a waypoint at the exact place you turn off a ridge, or get to some critical navigation feature. Take a photo, and associate that photo with the waypoint. Makes it much easier to describe a route to your friends, and gives you confidence- even when conditions have changed, and now its dark, or foggy. I love it.
Superb offline mapping, and great developer support.   In the UK it gives access to OS maps, so there is no need for anything else.  Update: Runs fine on Android 5.0 on my device (Nexus 4).
I tried about 8 different hiking app's the last few years. Yours is the best. You're the winner.
This is a great app. Can't speak highly enough of it. Works perfectly on Nexus 5 & 10 running Android 5. I use it regularly for Falconry and Hunting .

App is awesome. Super useful. Compass rotation stopped working after upgrade to Android 5.0. I downloaded a compass only app to verify and it works fine. I checked all my compass and rotation settings but nothing fixed the issue. Request you restore compass functionally as its critical to navigation. *Update* I removed and reinstalled the app again and it is now working.
replyContent: I am glad this has been resolved. I do believe that compass should work on Android 5.0 fine for most.

content: I've paid for the app on my galaxy note 3 and then paid extra for the version to go with my samsung gear s and it constantly doesn't work. Loads up fine on the phone but when I load it up on the gear s aswell to use the compass on the gear s for waypoints it more often than not doest load the map and the compass just freezes.  £10 down now for something I can't use :-(
replyContent: Contact us at the HelpDesk.

content: This app is not a plug & play type of app...it's so confusing and not user friendly...not at all!     I have never successfully been able to download an actual trail map or waypoints to follow on my phone...while using backcountry navigator.   It basically is nothing but a large topo map app and a waste of $12. I have communicated 3 times with the company via email and have remained thoroughly confused with their answers.   I'm an avid 2x through hiker of the Pacific Crest Trail and am aspiring to hike the CDT next year.  I was very excited to use this app and rave about it as well on my website, but that isn't going to happen. I'll be going back to my Garmin and it's ease of use and will loathe the fact I ever wasted my money on this app. Unless your the type of person that wants to spend days trying to figure this thing out...stay away!
replyContent: Waypoints and trails can be added in GPX or KML formats from many sites on the internet. We have offered you some solutions or resolution through the helpdesk and please respond.

content: Invaluable when I was deep in elk country.

I've used this app for the past 3 years now and it is a lifesaver.  Download the maps for areas you are planning to scout or hunt.  That way the maps will load regardless of cell service.  There are so many options for hunters to use this app.  Mark cameras, stands, travel routes, food sources, bedding areas, and more.  Then make notes and take a picture for future references if you'd like.  Buy it!!  You won't be disappointed.  Outstanding support from developer!
Best app ever, period.
Just what I was looking for.
Loading custom maps is great.
A very helpful app. Works great and since everything gets stored on your phone you don't need a data connection to use it. I highly recommend this app.
replyContent: Glad it is working well for you.

content: This is an outstanding app, well worth the price. Going to purchase it for my son also so I won't have to worry about him getting lost after dark.
I have tried many maps, and this is the tops for outdoors hunting etc.  I would like to see features in the future that will allow tracking of hunting buddies.  This would be a great add-on feature.
Don't waste your money . It does not work when you want it to...too complicated and over priced..
replyContent: Please write in to explain your dissatisfaction if you wish to request a refund.

content: I just used this on a hunting trip in Western Montana.  It was so good, others with Apple products asked to use my Android because it was so much better than what they had.  My Razr Maxx Battery lased two days in Airplane mode with no cell towers within 20 miles.  Then I used a charging pack to boost it for two more. Great Job!

I need an option to record the tracks in 1 second recording for time interval and 1 meter recording for the minimum distance. This setting makes better accuracy and precision in recording. Please update. Thank you very much.
The developer improves app on a regular basis. Its kml and gpx import is great. This is a must have hiking app. Worth every dollar.
Really good app, works great in the UK with Ordinance Survey map's I often inform the map readers where we actually are on the mountains
I am always impressed at how well this app works

What it lacks in robust festures that a true stand alone GPS offers, it more than makes up for in ease of use. Maps work without wifi or service and its pretty easy to catch an occasional ping that will keep you on track. Great for backpacking,  offers superior zoom capabilities and touchscreen just blows away button menue navigation. You will not regret purchasing this app. Add a robust external backup battery and you will still be well under the price for a cheapo GPS.
Used this a lot during walking holiday in Asturias (Picos de Europa) in June. Really good with GPS and free Spanish topo maps.

Got me out of a few tight spots in very remote area. Fog rolled in couldn't see 10 feet in fron of me. Then I remembered I had downloaded backwoods pro on my phone what's accurate within 3 feet love this app I have it on every one of my phones/tablets now.
Five stars if you can integrate NOAA maps or something with water depths. I have another program for water navigation but I can't cash maps. NOAA maps added, sweet! Five stars now.
It is a very nice GPS format for outdoorsman on your phone... Battery life is an issue how ever
replyContent: Be sure and join the newsletter because we are having some good discussions on this topic.

content: This app needs no cell service to work just the GPS in your tablet or phone
works like a charm
Specially because you can download maps.
Love it!

Awesome way to put a retired smart phone to use. I use this app in conjunction with my utv and a droid maxx HD too not only navigate but listen to music while driving. I get the occasional glitch but 99% of the time its the phones issue (other apps) great product. I'd buy it again without a thought.

This app. works great for the average to advanced outdoor enthusiast. Great support and rev. fixes. It's clear the developers care very much about what they do and not looking for a quick $$$ buck with an app. sale.  Chad Tempe, AZ

I've looked at other similar offerings, and this one stands out as a super star. It has a very good user interface and is very well presented. It is rich in features. It is also very accurate and very reliable. What a great tool it is to find your way through the back country. It is also a great "safety" item to help you return to your initial point or find other locations for extraction.Well done!

I have used BCN on several multi-day backpack trips through the Gila National Forest and the Big Bend National Park. My buddy carries a major brand name GPS. BCN on my Motorola Droid Razr is a superior system by far. It's readable in daylight, and I am able to download the latest maps for free just before leaving civilization.  To conserve battery, I put my Droid in airplane mode when I'm not using it. When I need the GPS, I bring it out of airplane mode until the Droid gets a GPS fix, then immediately put it back in airplane mode. So far, I've been able to squeeze four days' of trail use out of it without recharging.  Overall, I am very pleased with BCN. And the price is simply amazing. Thanks for a great product! October 2014 Update - Just finished a multi-day backpack to Rainbow Bridge. BCN was the map of choice - my buddy never even turned on his Garmin GPS! The battery in my new Droid Maxx easily lasted for four days in airplane mode with the GPS on. I am still very pleased with BCN and I recommend it to all my Realtor associates, too!

Major flaw: one cannot share a single waypoint. It appears as though you need to put waypoints in a "trip" folder, which is a collection of waypoints. Quite often I just want to share a single waypoint. Can you make this simple and important function available?
replyContent: Could you contact us at the helpdesk and tell us more about how it should be shared? With another person? Another app?

content: Used this for a hunt this weekend and it worked very well. Downloaded the topo maps for our area and used the app to follow ridges and mark the location of tracks etc. Highly recommended...does use a lot of battery if you leave your GPS on but I was able to use it all day by only getting occasional position fixes.
Nathan, The new menu layout is outstanding. I appreciate all the work you do. It is far and above better than my dedicated gps devices

I have been using this app since it appeared, firstly as a demo and them as a pro user. Its the best topo mapping app bar none. It has proven its worth both in the UK, Europe and now in Brazil.... and it keeps getting better. Top marks.
With this app there is no need to ever purchase a GPS. Topo maps are USGS, zoomable, etc.

I use this frequently in the UK. Once you hit on downloading tiles to use as your off line map then you are away. Especially helpful is the seamless change from the Ordnance Survey 1:50,000 to the OS 1:25,000 as you zoom in for greater detail. It can also be useful sometimes to get less detail by switching to OSM mapping. Also found it a valuable resource travelling abroad - little need for local maps. Geocachers may like to know that it can upload your PQs (and hide icons when not needed on another layer).

I have used this app hunting and so far so good. I am able to navigate in the thick woods I have never been to before without worrying about getting lost or how to get back to my vehicle. After buying a premium map I was able to get trail information within a wildlife management area in Texas. This was very helpful.

I have purchased this app about a year ago for a different phone.  It worked great.  After acquiring a Samsung s4 I tried downloading the BCNav from amazon app.  Wouldn't let me download. So I repurchased another from the play store.   App pops up upon request but no maps will load no matter what I choose.   So i was hoping if I purchased the accuterra it start working.  But no $31.00 Purchased twice and it's useless.   I have an overpriced compass that is actually the only thing working.  waste of money.
replyContent:
Matt, you did get a response. The full article is here. http://support.crittermap.com/entries/27671140-Samsung-Devices-External-Storage-locked-after-4-4-updates-
I have no way of further troubleshooting your issue unless you contact us.

content: Have taken it along on several hikes and has never failed me!
Love this app
Awesome
Works very well . Gives you great map layers for offline navigation .
I've used this app for hunting with no cell coverage and it's always worked well.  Like the ability to view topo or aerial!
Purchased this app instead of buying a gps device. Works great. Super easy to use on phone. Worth every penny.
Have been using this app for 2+ yrs. Kept me from getting lost more than once. On my wishlist would be a dawn/dusk calculator to incorporate my photography. Just a thought.
replyContent: Thank you. We just may do it.

content: I've tried several other apps for tracking my hikes and canoeing, and this app is the best.
The tracking and offline feature are essential.  Battery life is the only negative.
Awesome app, I trek on the forests of western Montana and this tracking feature keeps perfect track of my wanderings. Pretty easy to get turned around in the mountains

Update: had to unistall pro and trial and reinstall pro to get gps to work. I haved use this app for years going all the way back to the windows mobile days. Had the trial on this phone. But when forced to upgrade after not using for several month the latest version from 10/3/2014 gps aquire is broke. Can see satellites but never aquires even though all other apps obtain cords just fine.
replyContent: If GPS is acting flaky, rebooting the phone is usually sufficient to get it working again - and reinstalling is generally not necessary. There is also an option in settings to reset AGPS state or predownload it.

content: This app works so well that I ended up selling my standalone GPS unit and rely on my phone for navigation.
Been using this during off road trips for several months and it never disappoints.
As a mountain biker, going from paper maps to this app has been a revelation. Allowing me to navigate easily without having to buy an expensive addition device.
I use it while grouse hunting. It has a bunch of nice features.
Turn your cellphone in a high end GPS. Customizable and full of features.

After several years and three devices, this one is still above the fray. Constantly being developed and the news letter is often very informative. I even save some of them to my archives for future reference. You will not find a better outdoors map app. I still keep some of the others but this is my default.

I really like this app.  I use Backcountry Navigator more than any other app on my phone.  I have many saved maps for areas I spend time in.  It is great to be able to use my saved maps when I don't have cell coverage.  I export all of my tracks and waypoints for use in Google Earth.  I won't get an iphone for several reasons, but one of those reasons is that I can't use Backcountry Navigator.

I have been using Pro for several years now.  I'm camping every month with my Boy Scouts.  When going into the back country I use a GPS Sandbox tool on my computer to map my intended route.  Side load the gpx file to BC Navagator, download tiles for the area to my SD card and head out.  I record the hikes and then when home I export back to my sandbox tool.  I get a printout and graph of the hike, distance, elevation, everything. Print out and give a copy to the boys.   Using the Galaxy S4.  Great program.
Get app
I use this to map trails and various routes to locations. Current mapping, great close ups, easy to use.
I've never had any problems running this app across many platforms.
Great app

I use this for hunting navigation on my razor max phone and it is incredible. Does everything the developer says it will, and the email tips and tricks are outstanding. I understand it may have issues with other platforms or devices, but it works wonderfully for me. I couldn't be happier except for the inability to overlay tracks on a map on my laptop for study in a larger, more easily visible device. I still give five stars, though because it works as advertised. Please make the data tracks exportable.

Use it all the time for recording and navigating Jeep trails all over the west.   Incredible features, takes a little learning to unlock the potential.  very accurate and extremely useful.  love the support and frequent updates.

I use BackCountry Navigator for Search and Rescue.  I have it on an old phone that does not have mobile service and just pre-cache the maps for the whole county. In a recent search we did not have maps of the area. Before I got to the CP (Command Post) the team had hand drawn a map using a guide book as reference.   We had three teams in the field and the issue was, when they radioed in and gave us the UTM, we could not correlate that to the map.  Using BackCountry Navigator I was able to put the UTM in my phone and see the location on the Topo. From there I could plot the position on the hand drawn map to see what search areas we had covered.  Without it, we would not have been able to determine our search coverage. We did find the missing person after many hours of searching - the individual kept moving.   On a side note - if you are lost (and especially if you know people are looking for you) please stay put. It makes our job easier  Overall an awesome product. I can not recommend it highly enough,  thanks Nathan for all (the obvious) work you have put into this awesome product.

This thing is great.I've used it both for navigation and for stat tracking, and it hasn't let me down. Download the maps you want, head into the backcountry, and mark your points of interest (example: your car.) It'll help get ya back every time.  Also works well for tracking bike rides... I now have a Google Earth (KML) file with every bike ride I've done this year. Pretty neat.

Great app,  i love it.    I wish Canada had more downloadable maps,  or purchasable maps with land ownership etc.   Thank you Nathan Mellor.  A suggestion:      I would find it INCREDIBLY useful if i could use the app to see where my buddies are.    There are other apps that do this,  but i'd love to see it integrated in BackCountry  Navigator so that i can see where friends are in real time with an accuracy of within 10 m or better.

Have used out of cell coverage and worked brilliantly on gps satellites. New Zealand back country. Keep up the good work. 《That was 3 years ago.  I have now had backcountry pro on 4 phones and have found it flawless on each one galaxy s2 through to s5. For the price you can't beat it.  Also better then my Garmin GPS.  Screen is way better on my phone for one.  Good to see you're keeping up the good work.  😆
I have used this app all summer on miles of back country trails in WA. I still have much to learn but think this is a great tool for use in wilderness.
Es una porquería, no sirve para Puerto Rico.
replyContent: Si sirve. Se necesita escoger una mapa. Open Street Maps y Open Cycle Maps functiona.

content: This is a great app for many reasons! I personally use it to import my ranch map, and markings from Google Earth. Free topographic map access is also awesome! Worth the paid version IMHO.

I used this on a 4 day hike in Olympic NP. I was able to find very detailed maps for our trail. I had full knowledge of location, altitude, speed, time estimates for my next goal, and many other features. It's worth every penny.
Saved me so much money over buying a Garmin or Magellan. Having the GPS on can drain the battery of course so be sure to turn off when not in use. It helped get us back on route on Mt Shuksan

This app may need GPS Airtime to function properly on Droids.  Please bundle GPS Airtime with the paid version of Backcountry.  Had I but know this, I would not have posted on Verizon my question about Airplane mode and GPS functioning, and would have saved time on my recent trip to Colorado back country.  As it was, I had to discover the Airplane mode/GPS relationship on my own.   PS:  App works great on my RAZR MAXX, now that I have GPS Airtime and doesn't work for sour apples without it.
replyContent:
The vast majority of devices do not need GPS Airtime, and we cannot bundle it. Motorola, plus user reports, led us to believe that GPS Airtime would not make any difference on Razr Maxx. 
The phone companies are not any better about communicating their bugs to us than they are to the end users.

content: I use this app for recording ride tracks, tracking good fishing locations, where I see game while cruising around in my RZR. I love it because I have my camera, calling and text capability (if service permits) all in one small package. When on foot and concerned about battery life, I plug my phone into power storage. They are relatively cheap and slightly bigger than a stick of lip balm. Best of all, way less money spent even with the premium maps and overlays.

If you do everything right, this app does a great job. But it's not very intuitive and its hard to keep track of your tracks. App doesn't ask you to name the tracks so they're hard to find later. Developers seem to think you should poke through their entire manual before using this program, but who's going to do that?
Works great for navigating when out of data range.  Public lands boundries keep me where I'm supposed to be. Satellite imagery is a plus as well.
My most useful app when hunting elk

I bought the pro version a few years ago and loved it, then switched to an I phone, now that I came back to android with New phone I need to buy certain versions of maps I don't really care for having to pay for it twice, but either way it's still cheaper than a standalone GPS that has multiple  integrated maps
Best app so far worth every penny...  works great with the gear 2. My son takes the phone and I keep him on track with the watch....
replyContent:
It is happening for some people, including me, with unknown sources enabled.
If anyone experiences this problem, please complain to Samsung often and firmly. Their sabotage should not be tolerated.

content: Great App . Use it for ATV adventures . Nice to be able to use it with google earth an make routes on the big screen, then load it on my phone.
Back to 5 stars with the fix of storing maps to SD card.

I have been using this app for a few years for recording tracks and marking spots on lakes and river systems and I could not be happier with it. Especially now that the dev  added an option to display speed and direction on the map in real time (I requested that btw! :)) Thanks for the feature add and a great app!
replyContent: Glad it has been working on lakes and rivers.

content: Great App!
replyContent: There is no BLM data for any those states. But I do know that you would like an equivalent set of boundaries of public lands for those states. The Accuterra Maps might work as land types are color coded. Otherwise, we will try to meet your expectations someday.

content: Awesome app worth the money for the full version

Excellent app. Would be nice to have tones to let me know when I lose/regain satellite since I live in very mountainous terrain. I often used this app as a map and compass rather than a gps since sattelite signal was sketchy, nice that I had that option.
This is the best paid app I have on my phone. I use it almost every weekend, easy to use, great to always have a top map in my pocket.
Has full features, with excellent support. Continually improving. Been using it for many years. I can't say enough about it, and no, I don't own stock in the company...😃
I use this app to track my route, distance and speed when trail riding my horse.  Works well and i can compare tracks across multiple parks/trails.
Super simple and worlds amazing. Better than my dad's Garmin gps. Maps are great.

I no longer need to bother with paper maps when I hike. I can search locations I want to go to and track where I've been. Topo maps are crucial for hiking, and being able to save maps for out of coverage areas is important. I've been especially impressed with the concern and effort the developer continues to put into improving and supporting this excellent app.
Been using for a couple of years now, love it. Recommended to friends, who also love it... Wouldn't be without it, offline when were walking with my Nexus tab.

Used BackCountry Navigator to track my progress while hiking Half Dome. After 16 miles and 14 hours, my S4 still had 30% battery. And I was able to export my path to Google Earth without any problems.

Great GPS NAV program! I've been using the full paid version for over a year. SO worth it! Mostly for riding dirtbikes, adventure motorcycling.  When you are exploring, and want to find your way back quickly, you need something that works! Yes, there is a learning curve because this software is POWERFUL!   So, if you are serious about navigation, but not a $500 device, this is the software for you!

There are other choices out there, but none are as polished or complete as this one. Pound for pound, this one delivers! Android has got the iPhone beat (by far) when it comes to offline mapping. Galaxy Nexus / Galaxy Note 3
Use as my backup system along with my paper maps and compass. Use for every hiking and backpacking outing.
Have used this app all over the UK and Australia & it works perfectly. No issues so far!
Keeps getting better.
Works on my Motorola droids
Great App!!
If. you. like. maps. you will like this app. Just read the directions and the UI is fine. Most of the map data is free.

Used this app for 4 years now for offroad expeditions in Utah and Colorado. Totally dependable. Use it on a Samsung Note2 and since last year  on an Asus 8inch tablet for offroad navigating. The development team are super responsve and actually listen and build updates from customer feedback. Class act!
Awesome
Incredibly easy to use. I use it to hike. Quickly select and download cal topo maps free and use record track feature to track time, mileage, location etc. Most used app I have.
Nearly perfect.   Throw away your garmin
This is the best app I have found!

I am a volunteer member of my county search and rescue team, so accurate tracking is important. This app does everything that the $500 Garmins do, and much more easily. It is easily the best GPS mapper in the Play Store.
replyContent: NAD83 is an option in settings.

content: Best backcountry navigation app I've found on any of the mobile OSs. Awesome stuff.
I use this app on every remote fire I jump. It's awesome.

Used it while canoe paddling on the Green River in North Carolina last weekend. It helped in finding the channel in lake Adger and navigating with the current, which makes estimating distance covered tricky.
I have used some different apps they do not compare to BackCountry!
works, recommend.
This developer really maintains this app well. He has a great blog to go along with it. He hikes and uses his own app.  Money very well spent!  THANKS!
It just works, I like it better than my GPS I spent $300 on

While going on a back woods hike.  No trail just bush wacking.   The pro app stopped operation several times.  I rebooted my g5 4 or 5 times during the hike.  At the halfway mark the gps stopped working (I had clear access to the sky I was not in a valley).  Several time I compaired the  compass  agaist a real compass at times it was up to 35 degrees off.  I knew the area I was hiking so I was not too concerned.  If I was in an unfamiliar area I would have been lost.
replyContent: Please contact us at the helpdesk if you would like to diagnose.

content: I love the topo graphs

I had used BCNAV on my Motorola Triumph, and while it ran OK, the poor screen quality kept me from using it much. On my new Samsung Galaxy S5, it works great! Tracking has been spot on.  Thanks for a great product.
It is the best of its kind.
Perfect for hiking, climbing, etc. Download topos and imagery!

Uk use - excellent way of browsing OS 1:25000 and 1:50000 maps. Areas can be selected for download and used offline when out in the mountains. Amazingly, there is no per tile subscription or fee for this service - a different model to the OS's own very expensive app, which I guess has extra functionalities - but hey, I don't need them.
